    "title": "Muleshoe, Abernathy, Hale Center, and Lockney Water Systems: Russian hackers caused water tank overflow via SCADA",
    "summary": "In January 2024, Russian hacktivist group CARR (Cyber Army of Russia Reborn) accessed SCADA systems at four small Texas water utilities — Muleshoe, Abernathy, Hale Center, and Lockney — causing a water tank in Muleshoe to overflow and manipulating pump controls at others. The FBI, CISA, and EPA issued a joint advisory warning about Russian threat actors targeting water infrastructure. The attacks demonstrated that even small rural utilities are viable targets for nation-state hacktivists.",
