    "source_url": "https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa24-057a",
    "date": "2024-01-18",
    "severity": "critical",
    "featured": true,
    "industry": "SLED",
    "enriched_summary": "On January 18, 2024, the Cyber Army of Russia Reborn (CARR) — a unit linked to Russia's GRU military intelligence — compromised the Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) system at Muleshoe via a third-party vendor's remote login interface for industrial software, causing a water tank to overflow for 30–45 minutes before operators took the hacked system offline and switched to manual control. Concurrent attacks targeted nearby utilities in Abernathy, Hale Center, and Lockney; Muleshoe's tank overflow was the only successful physical disruption, with Hale Center repelling the firewall breach attempt and Lockney detecting suspicious activity before damage occurred.",
