    "summary": "On September 29, 2018, Otsego County detected that hackers had infiltrated county government computers through a remote desktop server at a county employee's home and were using the county's processing power to mine cryptocurrency, causing systems to run extremely slowly and taking the county website offline. New York state's Cyber Incident Response Team arrived and cut off the hackers' access within two hours, with no evidence that financial or personal data was viewed or manipulated.",
