    "summary": "Beginning February 21, 2018, SamSam ransomware infected more than 2,000 Windows-based computers across CDOT offices statewide, then re-infected with a mutated variant during recovery. Governor Hickenlooper declared the first governor-declared cyber emergency in U.S. history on March 1; the attack ultimately compromised 1,274 laptops, 427 desktops, 339 servers, 158 databases, 154 software applications, and all VoIP phones across 200 CDOT locations. The state refused to pay the ransom; recovery cost approximately $1.5 million with the governor authorizing up to $2 million.",
