    "title": "PIH Health: Phishing attack compromises 45 employee email accounts, 189,763 patient records exposed",
    "summary": "In June 2019, a targeted phishing campaign compromised 45 employee email accounts at PIH Health, a California healthcare network operating hospitals, urgent care centers, and a multispecialty physician group across Los Angeles and Orange Counties. The breach exposed names, addresses, SSNs, diagnoses, lab results, medications, and financial information of 189,763 individuals. PIH failed to report to HHS OCR until January 2020 — 7 months late — and ultimately settled HIPAA violations for $600,000 in 2023.",
