    "title": "San Diego Family Care: Ransomware Attack via Vendor Netgain Exposes 125K Patient Records",
    "summary": "In December 2020, the IT hosting provider for San Diego Family Care (an FQHC) and Health Center Partners of Southern California was hit by a ransomware attack perpetrated by the Netgain Technology threat actors. San Diego Family Care learned in January 2021 that certain data may have been accessed, and on May 7, 2021 notified approximately 125,530 affected individuals. Compromised data included names, Social Security numbers, and insurance claims information. A class action lawsuit settled for $1 million.",
    "source_url": "https://databreaches.net/2021/05/08/san-diego-family-care-discloses-possible-data-breach/",
    "source_name": "DataBreaches.Net",
    "date": "2021-01-20",
    "severity": "high",
    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Physician Group / Clinic",
    "healthcare_sector": "Ambulatory / Outpatient",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "In December 2020, Netgain Technology — an IT hosting and managed services vendor — suffered a ransomware attack that compromised data for multiple healthcare clients, including San Diego Family Care, a Federally Qualified Health Center providing medical, dental, and mental health services. Netgain reportedly paid a $2.3 million ransom to obtain decryption keys and prevent further data disclosure. San Diego Family Care learned in January 2021 that patient data may have been accessed and notified approximately 125,530 affected patients in May 2021. The total affected count was later revised to 154,513. Exposed data included names, Social Security numbers, financial account numbers, dates of birth, diagnoses, health insurance information, and client identification numbers. A $1 million class action settlement was reached.",
