    "title": "Pabalan Eye Center: Ransomware Attack on Riverside Ophthalmology Practice Affects 50K Patients",
    "summary": "Francisco J. Pabalan, M.D., doing business as Pabalan Eye Center, a physician group practice in Riverside, California, suffered a ransomware attack between May 1–3, 2021 that encrypted servers containing patient data. The practice notified approximately 50,000 patients that their protected health information — including scanned insurance forms, exam findings, medical imaging, diagnostic testing, and past medical records — was potentially exposed. No ransom was paid; the practice restored its network from clean backups and reported the incident to HHS OCR.",
