    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between May 1–3, 2021, ransomware actors encrypted the servers of Pabalan Eye Center, a physician group practice in Riverside, California, locking down patient records. The practice did not pay the ransom and instead restored its network from clean backup data after reformatting all servers and computers, resetting all passwords, and implementing updated operating systems and a new VPN. Approximately 50,000 patients were notified that protected health information — including scanned insurance forms, exam findings, medical imaging, diagnostic testing, and scanned past medical records — was potentially exposed. The practice determined the attack appeared to be financially motivated via ransomware rather than targeted data theft.",
