    "summary": "On January 5, 2021, Granite Wellness Centers, a network of nonprofit substance use disorder treatment centers operating across Placer, Nevada, and Yuba counties in Northern California, was struck by a ransomware attack that encrypted patient records. The attack was detected in progress and systems were taken offline; no ransom was paid as files were restored from backups. Up to 15,600 patients were affected, with data including names, dates of birth, addresses, treatments, medical histories, health insurance information, SSNs, and bank account numbers potentially exposed. A class action lawsuit settled for $725,000.",
