    "summary": "Marin Community Clinics, a Federally Qualified Health Center serving Marin County in Northern California, was hit by a ransomware attack in April 2021 that locked down its computer systems. The clinic paid an undisclosed ransom at the advice of its network operator to obtain decryption keys. While the CEO stated no patient data was compromised, the Marin Healthcare District and Prima Medical Foundation notified more than 5,000 patients that some medical data may have been lost during the recovery process. The attack forced the clinic to operate on paper records for several days.",
