    "enriched_summary": "Marin Community Clinics, a Federally Qualified Health Center serving Marin County in Northern California, was struck by a ransomware attack on the evening of April 21, 2021, that locked down its computer systems and kept them unavailable through late Friday afternoon — approximately two days of downtime. At the advice of its network operator Marin Medical Practices Concepts, a ransom of an undisclosed amount was paid to restore access. During the outage, the clinic operated entirely on paper records for patient care. The Marin Healthcare District and Prima Medical Foundation subsequently notified more than 5,000 patients that some medical data may have been lost during the recovery process due to a technical glitch.",
