    "title": "Partnership HealthPlan of California: Hive Ransomware Attack Disrupts Operations for 854,913 Beneficiaries",
    "summary": "On March 19, 2022, the Hive ransomware group attacked Partnership HealthPlan of California, a nonprofit Medi-Cal managed care plan serving over 610,000 beneficiaries across 14 northern California counties, claiming to have exfiltrated 400 GB of data. The attack disrupted the organization's ability to process Treatment Authorization Requests, forcing hospitals and providers to proceed without prior authorization. PHC confirmed the breach affected 854,913 individuals and began sending notification letters in May 2022; a class action lawsuit was filed in Humboldt County Superior Court on May 5, 2022.",
    "source_url": "https://therecord.media/hive-ransomware-shuts-down-california-health-care-organization",
    "source_name": "The Record (Recorded Future News)",
    "date": "2022-03-19",
