    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Physician Group / Clinic",
    "healthcare_sector": "Ambulatory / Outpatient",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On March 19, 2022, the Hive ransomware group attacked Partnership HealthPlan of California — a nonprofit Medi-Cal managed care plan serving over 610,000 beneficiaries across 14 northern California counties — exfiltrating 400 GB of data before encrypting file servers. The attack disrupted PHC's ability to process Treatment Authorization Requests (TARs), forcing hospitals and providers to perform procedures without prior authorization and complete paperwork retroactively, creating significant operational and reimbursement risk across the provider network. PHC did not disclose the ransomware attack when its website went down, acknowledging only 'anomalous network activity' when the site was restored on April 15. PHC confirmed the breach affected 854,913 individuals and a class action lawsuit was filed in Humboldt County Superior Court on May 5, 2022.",
