    "title": "Smile Brands Inc.: Malware Attack Exposes Data of Up to 2.59 Million Dental Patients",
    "summary": "Irvine, California-based Smile Brands, one of the largest dental support organizations in the United States, confirmed that malware on its network allowed unauthorized access to patient data between January 18, 2022 and February 24, 2022. The investigation, completed April 4, 2022, determined that the breach affected up to 2,592,494 individuals across the dental practices it supports. Compromised data included names, SSNs, dates of birth, financial account information, medical and prescription records, and health insurance information.",
