    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Smile Brands Inc., an Irvine, California-based dental support organization operating practices nationwide, discovered a ransomware attack on approximately April 24, 2021 in which unauthorized actors had accessed its servers and exfiltrated patient data. The investigation — completed April 4, 2022 — ultimately determined the breach affected up to 2,592,494 individuals, though the initial HHS OCR report in October 2021 listed only 1,200 affected, later revised to 199,683 before reaching the final figure. Compromised data included names, SSNs, dates of birth, financial account information, medical and prescription records, and health insurance information. A class action settlement received final court approval on January 16, 2024, with defendants also investing in excess of $4.5 million in enhanced security measures.",
