    "summary": "On December 1, 2022, ransomware actors gained access to servers shared by Regal Medical Group, Lakeside Medical Organization, ADOC Acquisition Co. (A Medical Group), and Greater Covina Medical Group — all part of the Heritage Provider Network in Southern California. Employees noticed technical difficulties on December 2; the breach was confirmed December 8, 2022. Regal notified HHS OCR on February 1, 2023, disclosing that 3,300,638 patients' names, SSNs, dates of birth, diagnoses, lab results, radiology reports, prescriptions, and health plan numbers were stolen. More than 25 class action lawsuits were filed; a $49.99 million settlement received preliminary court approval in 2025.",
