    "summary": "On March 14, 2023, Petaluma Health Center — a Federally Qualified Health Center (FQHC) operating nine clinics in Sonoma County, California — detected unauthorized access to its network. The Karakurt ransomware group claimed responsibility, reporting they had paid for access to the already-compromised system, then exfiltrated credentials and patient data. Nearly 125,000 individuals' names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, health insurance, and medical information were potentially acquired. Petaluma Health Center notified patients beginning June 1, 2023, and filed with HHS OCR and the California Attorney General.",
