    "title": "La Clinica de La Raza: Employee Email Accounts Breached, 15,316 Patients Affected",
    "summary": "Between January 24 and February 8, 2023, unauthorized parties accessed multiple employee email accounts at La Clinica de La Raza, a Federally Qualified Health Center (FQHC) operating 35 locations across Oakland and the East Bay, serving over 90,000 patients annually. The breach exposed names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, financial account information, medical treatment information, and health insurance information for 15,316 patients. La Clinica filed a notice of data breach with HHS OCR on April 7, 2023; a class action lawsuit and settlement followed.",
