    "title": "Rancho Family Medical Group: Vendor (KMJ Health Solutions) Breach Affects 10,480 Patients",
    "summary": "On November 19, 2023, KMJ Health Solutions — a vendor providing online signout and charge capture systems to Rancho Family Medical Group, a primary care physician group in Southern California — suffered a security incident that exposed patient data. KMJ could not determine exactly which records were accessed because the impacted data was wiped and unrecoverable. Rancho Family Medical Group was notified on January 11, 2024, and subsequently reported 10,480 affected individuals to HHS OCR (filing date March 2024). Exposed data included names, dates of birth, medical record numbers, treatment locations, dates of service, and procedure codes. A $315,000 class action settlement was later agreed.",
