    "title": "Providence Medical Institute: $240,000 OCR civil monetary penalty imposed in 2024 for HIPAA failures stemming from ransomware attack",
    "summary": "Providence Medical Institute (PMI), a large Southern California medical practice with 275 providers across 35 offices, was hit by ransomware on February 18, 2018 after an employee clicked a phishing link, encrypting ePHI of 85,000 individuals belonging to its acquired subsidiary Center for Orthopaedic Specialists. OCR issued a Notice of Proposed Determination in March 2024 and a Notice of Final Determination in July 2024, imposing a $240,000 civil monetary penalty for two HIPAA Security Rule violations: failure to maintain a business associate agreement and failure to implement policies restricting ePHI access to authorized users. OCR reduced the penalty by $60,000 because PMI demonstrated 12 consecutive months of recognized security practices prior to the attack.",
