    "summary": "The Elizabeth Hospice, a nonprofit hospice serving communities in Escondido, San Diego, Carlsbad, and Temecula, California, discovered an unresponsive server on November 2, 2022, and confirmed that an unauthorized individual had accessed the network. An internal investigation found that an employee had forwarded business email to a personal account, exposing patient first and last names, dates of admission and discharge, patient account numbers, and basic health information for 35,496 current and former patients. Notification letters were sent on December 14, 2022.",
