    "title": "Heritage Provider Network / Pacific Family Hospice / Valley's Best Hospice: Ransomware Attack Exposes 3.3M Patient Records",
    "summary": "A ransomware attack on the Heritage Provider Network in December 2022 compromised the protected health information of approximately 3,300,638 individuals. The attack, first detected on December 2, 2022, affected multiple California-affiliated entities including Pacific Family Hospice (Anaheim, CA) and Valley's Best Hospice, with breach notifications sent to patients in February 2023 and reported to HHS OCR on February 10, 2023. Data exposed included names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, diagnoses, lab results, prescription information, and radiology reports. A $49.99 million class action settlement was reached naming both hospice entities as defendants.",
