    "title": "Archer Health (Carlsbad, CA): Unprotected database exposes ~145,000 patient files",
    "summary": "On September 26, 2025, cybersecurity researcher Jeremiah Fowler discovered a publicly accessible, unencrypted, password-free 23.7 GB database belonging to Archer Health Inc., a home health and palliative care provider based in Carlsbad, California. The database contained approximately 145,596 files including patient names, Social Security numbers, medical record numbers, addresses, phone numbers, discharge summaries, home health certifications, and care plan documents. Archer Health secured the database within hours of notification; the organization subsequently reported the incident to HHS OCR as affecting 4,285 individuals.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hipaajournal.com/home-health-care-database-exposed-online/",
