    "title": "PIH Health (Whittier, CA): Ransomware attack disrupts home health and hospice operations",
    "summary": "Beginning December 1, 2024, a ransomware attack hit PIH Health, a Southern California health network, with the threat actor retaining network access from November 14, 2024 through December 23, 2024. The attack disrupted PIH Health's hospitals, urgent care centers, physicians' offices, and specifically its home health and hospice agency, forcing staff to use personal phones and handwritten records. The attackers claimed exfiltration of approximately 17 million patient records (unverified by PIH Health); the confirmed breach scope — including names, SSNs, medical records, financial data — was reported to HHS and patient notification letters were completed in February 2026 after the full affected list was identified in December 2025.",
