    "title": "VITAS Hospice Services (national, California AG notified): Month-long vendor account intrusion affects 319,177 patients",
    "summary": "Between September 21 and October 27, 2025, an unauthorized actor compromised a third-party vendor account and used it to access VITAS Hospice Services' systems — a breach not discovered until October 24, 2025. VITAS, the largest for-profit hospice chain in the U.S., notified the California and Texas attorneys general, and reported the breach to HHS OCR on November 24, 2025, listing 319,177 individuals affected nationwide. Compromised data may include names, SSNs, driver's license numbers, dates of birth, diagnosis, medications, lab results, treatment information, and health insurance details. Multiple class action lawsuits were filed and law firms launched investigations; VITAS offered 24 months of complimentary credit monitoring to affected individuals.",
