    "enriched_summary": "Between September 21 and October 27, 2025, an unauthorized actor compromised a vendor account and used it to access VITAS Hospice Services' systems for over a month before the breach was discovered on October 24, 2025. VITAS — the largest for-profit hospice chain in the U.S. — had 319,177 patients' protected health information exposed, including Social Security numbers, diagnoses, medications, and lab results. The company notified the California and Texas attorneys general, reported the incident to HHS OCR on November 24, 2025, and offered 24 months of credit monitoring, while multiple class action lawsuits were filed across several states.",
