    "title": "Enhabit Home Health & Hospice (national, California AG notified): Doctor Alliance vendor breach exposes 23,154 patients",
    "summary": "Between October 31–November 6, 2025 and November 14–17, 2025, an unauthorized party used compromised credentials to access the Doctor Alliance platform — a billing/care-coordination tool used by Enhabit Home Health & Hospice — and viewed or copied patient records. Doctor Alliance informed Enhabit on December 5, 2025; Enhabit filed with HHS OCR on February 5, 2026 listing 23,154 affected individuals. The California Attorney General was among those notified. Exposed data included names, addresses, dates of birth, physician names, medical record numbers, clinical information, and health plan numbers (no SSNs or financial data exposed). Enhabit terminated its relationship with Doctor Alliance and offered Experian credit monitoring to affected individuals.",
