    "title": "BAYADA Home Health Care (national, California operations): Doctor Alliance vendor breach exposes client PHI",
    "summary": "On December 4, 2025, BAYADA Home Health Care was notified that its third-party vendor Doctor Alliance suffered unauthorized access to its platform between October 31–November 6, 2025 and November 14–17, 2025, with the Kazu ransomware group claiming to have stolen 353 GB / 1.24 million files from Doctor Alliance. BAYADA's own systems were not compromised, but Home Health Certification and Plan of Care forms for a limited number of clients — including names, dates of birth, diagnoses, treatment information, and health insurance details — were potentially accessed. BAYADA operates extensively in California; the company discontinued use of Doctor Alliance and offered Experian credit monitoring to affected individuals.",
