    "summary": "VITAS Hospice Services, LLC, the largest for-profit hospice chain in the U.S., suffered a month-long network intrusion between September 21 and October 27, 2025, discovered October 24, 2025, via a compromised third-party vendor account. The breach exposed the PHI of 319,177 individuals — including names, SSNs, diagnoses, medications, lab results, and treatment information — across multiple states including California. The company notified the California Attorney General on November 19, 2025, mailed patient notifications in late November 2025, and was hit with class action lawsuits (including California claims) through early 2026. Texas alone confirmed 5,633 residents affected; California notification letters were issued per the CA AG filing.",
