    "summary": "On October 10, 2021, Community Medical Centers—a nonprofit serving low-income patients across Northern California's San Joaquin, Solano, and Yolo counties—detected unusual network activity and shut down its entire IT network as a precaution. The ransomware incident compromised PHI of 656,047 patients, including names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, and medical information. Breach notification letters were sent November 2, 2021.",
