    "enriched_summary": "On October 10, 2021, Community Medical Centers — a nonprofit Federally Qualified Health Center network serving low-income patients across California's San Joaquin, Solano, and Yolo counties — detected unusual activity on its network and immediately shut down the entire IT infrastructure as a precaution. The ransomware attack compromised protected health information for 656,047 patients, making it one of the largest community health center breaches in California history. The exposed data included highly sensitive information including names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, and medical records. Breach notifications were mailed to affected patients on November 2, 2021.",
