    "title": "Barlow Respiratory Hospital (Los Angeles): Vice Society Ransomware Attack",
    "summary": "On August 27, 2021, the Vice Society ransomware gang attacked Barlow Respiratory Hospital in Los Angeles, gaining access to the network and electronic medical record system and exfiltrating patient data before encryption. Files containing PHI of 9,880 individuals were posted on Vice Society's dark web leak site; data included patient names, clinical information, and employee disciplinary records. The hospital continued operating under emergency procedures and a class action lawsuit settlement was reached.",
