    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On August 27, 2021 — just one day before the Vice Society attack on United Health Centers — the same ransomware group infiltrated Barlow Respiratory Hospital in Los Angeles, gained access to the electronic medical record system, and exfiltrated patient and employee data before encrypting files. Files containing PHI of 9,880 individuals, including clinical information and employee disciplinary records, were posted on Vice Society's dark web leak site. The hospital continued operations under emergency procedures during recovery. A class action lawsuit was subsequently filed and a settlement was reached.",
