    "summary": "LifeLong Medical Care, an East Bay California community health provider, was impacted by a November 2020 ransomware attack on its IT vendor Netgain Technologies. An investigation concluded February 25, 2021 confirmed unauthorized access to patient data; LifeLong notified 115,448 affected patients in August 2021 and reported the breach to HHS OCR. Compromised data included names, Social Security numbers, birthdates, patient cardholder numbers, and treatment/diagnosis information.",
