    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "In November 2020, Netgain Technologies — an IT managed services provider — suffered a ransomware attack that gave attackers access to the systems and data of numerous healthcare clients, including LifeLong Medical Care, an East Bay California community health network. Netgain paid the ransom and received assurances that stolen data was deleted, but an investigation completed February 25, 2021 confirmed unauthorized access to LifeLong patient data. The breach exposed PHI for 115,448 patients including names, Social Security numbers, birthdates, patient cardholder numbers, and treatment information. LifeLong did not notify affected patients until August 2021 — approximately nine months after the original breach.",
