    "enriched_summary": "On January 28, 2021, malware was discovered on patient databases at La Clinica de La Raza, a Federally Qualified Health Center in Oakland serving predominantly Latino communities across Alameda, Contra Costa, and Solano counties. Attackers had access to patient database systems from January 28 through February 4, 2021 — a week-long window before access was severed. A forensic investigation confirmed the breach on February 26, 2021, and the incident was reported to HHS OCR as affecting 31,132 individuals. Exposed data included names, addresses, dates of birth, diagnostic codes, appointment details, and in some cases Social Security numbers.",
