    "summary": "On October 2, 2022, CommonSpirit Health — the second-largest nonprofit Catholic health system in the US, formed by the 2019 merger of Catholic Health Initiatives and Dignity Health — suffered a major ransomware attack that forced systems offline across 164 facilities in 13 states. The attack disrupted EHR access, payroll systems, and patient care operations, costing an estimated $160 million. The breach ultimately exposed the personal health information of 623,774 patients. CommonSpirit confirmed Dignity Health facilities in California experienced minimal direct impact, though the broader network disruption affected operations nationwide.",
