    "org_type": "Hospital / Health System",
    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On October 2, 2022, CommonSpirit Health — the second-largest nonprofit Catholic health system in the US with 142 hospitals and 700+ care sites in 21 states — suffered a major ransomware attack that forced electronic health records and critical systems offline across 164 facilities in 13 states. The operational disruption lasted weeks, affecting patient scheduling, payroll processing, and clinical workflows as staff resorted to manual paper processes. Total losses were estimated at approximately $160 million. The breach ultimately compromised the PHI of 623,774 patients. Dignity Health facilities in California, which are part of the CommonSpirit network, experienced operational disruptions from the broader network shutdown.",
