    "title": "San Gorgonio Memorial Hospital: Unauthorized Network Access Exposes Patient Data",
    "summary": "Between October 29 and November 10, 2022, an unauthorized party gained access to the internal computer network of San Gorgonio Memorial Hospital, a 79-bed nonprofit facility in Banning, California. Electronic records systems were shut down for six days as a result, forcing staff to revert to handwritten notes. Compromised data included patient names, addresses, dates of birth, medical record numbers, visit IDs, health insurance information, and in some cases Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, and financial account information. A class action settlement of $800,000 was later reached.",
    "source_url": "https://therecord.media/california-hospital-breach-exposed-patients-social-security-numbers-medical-info",
