    "date": "2022-10-29",
    "severity": "high",
    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Hospital / Health System",
    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between October 29 and November 10, 2022, an unauthorized party gained persistent access to the internal computer network of San Gorgonio Memorial Hospital, a 79-bed nonprofit facility in Banning, California in Riverside County. Upon detection on November 10, the hospital shut down its electronic records systems for approximately six days, forcing clinical staff to revert to handwritten notes for all documentation. The breach exposed a broad range of patient data including Social Security numbers, financial account information, and clinical details for an undisclosed number of patients. A third-party forensic firm was engaged for investigation, and the hospital later reached an $800,000 class action settlement.",
