    "summary": "On or around February 19, 2022, ransomware attackers gained access to the IT systems of Livingston Memorial VNA Health Corporation, a Ventura, California-based provider of home health and hospice services, and encrypted files. Investigators confirmed that attackers had accessed patient data prior to encryption. The HHS Office for Civil Rights breach portal records 34,775 affected individuals. Breach notification letters were delayed until January 2023 due to the complexity of identifying affected individuals.",
