    "title": "Medical Eye Services (MESVision): MOVEit Exploit by Clop Group Exposes 346,828 Patient Records",
    "summary": "California-based Medical Eye Services, Inc. (MESVision), a vision benefits management provider serving Blue Shield of California members, had 346,828 individuals' protected health information stolen via the MOVEit Transfer zero-day vulnerability exploited by the Clop ransomware group between May 28–31, 2023. MESVision discovered the breach on August 23, 2023, and notified HHS in November 2023. Exposed data included names, SSNs, birth dates, insurance policy numbers, subscriber IDs, claim numbers, and group numbers.",
