    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between May 28 and May 31, 2023, the Clop ransomware cartel exploited a zero-day vulnerability in the MOVEit Transfer file-sharing platform to steal data from Medical Eye Services (MESVision), a California-based vision benefits manager serving Blue Shield of California members. MESVision did not discover the breach until August 23, 2023, and notified HHS in November 2023 — a nearly three-month gap that drew scrutiny given how quickly other MOVEit victims disclosed. The attack exposed the personal and insurance information of 346,828 vision plan members, including names, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, subscriber and member IDs, and policy and claim numbers. In response, MESVision rebuilt its MOVEit server, deployed additional technical safeguards, and arranged free credit monitoring through Kroll for affected individuals.",
