    "title": "L.A. Care Health Plan: $1.3 Million HIPAA Settlement for Multiple Security Failures",
    "summary": "On September 11, 2023, HHS OCR announced a $1.3 million HIPAA settlement with L.A. Care Health Plan — the nation's largest publicly operated health plan serving 2.7 million Los Angeles County residents — resolving two separate breach investigations. The first stemmed from a 2014 incident where members could view other members' PHI through the online payment portal; the second involved a 2019 mailing error sending ID cards containing PHI to wrong members. OCR found failures to conduct adequate risk analysis and implement security evaluations. A three-year corrective action plan was imposed.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hhs.gov/about/news/2023/09/11/hhs-office-civil-rights-settles-with-la-care-health-plan-potential-hipaa-security-rule-violations.html",
