    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "HHS OCR announced a $1.3 million HIPAA settlement with L.A. Care Health Plan — the nation's largest publicly operated health plan serving 2.7 million Los Angeles County residents — resolving two separate long-running investigations. The first stemmed from a January 2014 online payment portal misconfiguration that allowed members to see other members' names, addresses, and member IDs; the second involved a 2019 mailing error sending ID cards with PHI to wrong members. OCR found systemic failures to conduct adequate risk analyses, perform periodic security evaluations, and maintain proper access controls — characterizing the compliance failures as representing years of neglect across both the Privacy and Security Rules. In addition to the financial penalty, L.A. Care agreed to a three-year corrective action plan requiring an enterprise-wide risk analysis and new HIPAA-specific policies, procedures, and training.",
