    "summary": "In January 2023, HHS OCR settled a HIPAA right of access investigation with Sharp HealthCare, doing business as Sharp Rees-Stealy Medical Centers (SRMC), a San Diego-based health system. SRMC agreed to pay $70,000 and implement a corrective action plan after failing to provide timely access to patient medical records as required under HIPAA's right of access standard. This was OCR's sixteenth enforcement action under its HIPAA Right of Access Initiative.",
