    "title": "PIH Health: Ransomware attack claims 17 million patient records, 3-hospital system disrupted",
    "summary": "On December 1, 2024, ransomware hit PIH Health's network, taking down EHR, pharmacy, radiology, laboratory, and most phone systems at PIH Health Downey Hospital, PIH Health Whittier Hospital, and PIH Health Good Samaritan Hospital, as well as urgent care, home health, hospice, and physician offices across the San Gabriel Valley and Orange County. Staff reverted to paper-based downtime procedures; hackers claimed exfiltration of ~2 TB of data including 17 million patient records with PHI, SSNs, financial data, diagnoses, photos, and patient emails. The FBI and local law enforcement were engaged; forensic investigation confirmed threat-actor access from November 14 through December 23, 2024. Patient notification letters were sent February 25, 2026; class action litigation followed.",
