    "title": "Kaiser Permanente: Web-tracker impermissible disclosure of PHI to Google Ads, 13.4 million members",
    "summary": "Kaiser Permanente disclosed in April 2024 that tracking technologies (Google Analytics, Microsoft Bing, and X/Twitter pixels) embedded in its websites and mobile apps transmitted member data to third-party advertisers from April 2021 through January 2024. Exposed data included names, IP addresses, sign-in status, search terms in the health encyclopedia, and navigation behavior—but not SSNs or financial data. The breach affected 13.4 million current and former members across California and multiple other states and was reported to HHS OCR on April 12, 2024. Kaiser Permanente agreed to a $47.5 million class action settlement.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hipaajournal.com/kaiser-permanente-website-tracker-breach-affects-13-4-million-individuals/",
