    "title": "Watsonville Community Hospital: Termite ransomware attack, entire patient database accessed",
    "summary": "On November 25–30, 2024, ransomware group Termite (using a modified Babuk variant) accessed Watsonville Community Hospital's network. Network disruption was detected on November 29; staff reverted to paper charts and manual prescriptions while the ER remained open but with patient delays. Stolen data included names, DOBs, SSNs, passport numbers, driver's license numbers, addresses, and diagnosis information. Termite added the hospital to its dark web leak site on December 11, 2024. The hospital began mailing breach notifications on October 15, 2025; employees separately reported tax refund fraud attributed to the breach.",
