    "enriched_summary": "Between November 25 and November 30, 2024, the Termite ransomware group — using a modified Babuk variant — gained access to Watsonville Community Hospital's network in a Thanksgiving-period attack. The hospital detected the network disruption on November 29 and reverted to paper charts and manual prescriptions while keeping the ER operational, though patient care faced delays. Termite added the hospital to its dark web leak site on December 11, 2024, and subsequently dumped unencrypted PHI including more than 150 images of patients' insurance cards and driver's licenses, along with extensive demographic and clinical data spanning 2021-2024. Notifications were initially sent starting December 30, 2024, but the file review was not completed until September 22, 2025, with final notification letters mailed October 15, 2025. Approximately 20 employees subsequently reported identity theft and fraudulent tax return filings attributed to the breach.",
