    "title": "Cedars-Sinai Medical Center: Anonymous Sudan DDoS attack forces 8-hour ER diversion",
    "summary": "In February 2024, the hacktivist-for-hire group Anonymous Sudan launched a large-scale DDoS attack against Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles, taking down the hospital's emergency department systems and forcing incoming patients to be diverted to other facilities for approximately eight hours. The attack caused significant operational disruption but did not result in a confirmed patient data exfiltration. In October 2024, the U.S. Department of Justice indicted two Sudanese brothers (Ahmed Salah Yousif Omer and Alaa Salah Yusuuf Omer) for their roles in conducting more than 35,000 DDoS attacks globally, including this attack.",
