    "enriched_summary": "In February 2024, hacktivist-for-hire group Anonymous Sudan launched a large-scale DDoS attack against Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles using their proprietary Distributed Cloud Attack Tool (DCAT), nicknamed 'Godzilla,' forcing incoming emergency patients to be diverted to other facilities for approximately eight hours. The attack did not result in confirmed patient data exfiltration but caused significant operational disruption to one of the country's most prominent academic medical centers. In October 2024, the U.S. Department of Justice indicted two Sudanese brothers — Ahmed Salah Yousif Omer (age 22) and Alaa Salah Yusuuf Omer (age 27) — who ran Anonymous Sudan as a criminal attack-for-hire service that launched over 35,000 DDoS attacks globally, including at least 70 targeting computers in the Los Angeles area, causing more than $10 million in total damages to U.S. victims.",
