    "title": "LA County Department of Public Health: Phishing attack exposes 200,000+ residents' data",
    "summary": "Between February 19–20, 2024, a threat actor used phishing emails to steal login credentials of 53 LA County Department of Public Health employees, gaining access to their email accounts. The compromised accounts contained personally identifiable information and protected health information for over 200,000 individuals, including names, DOBs, SSNs, diagnoses, prescriptions, medical record numbers, health insurance data, and financial information. The breach was publicly disclosed in June 2024 following a law enforcement investigation. DPH disabled accounts, re-imaged devices, and offered one year of free identity monitoring to affected individuals.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hipaajournal.com/los-angeles-county-department-public-health-phishing-attack/",
