    "healthcare_sector": "Public Health Agency",
    "sled_sector": "County Government",
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between February 19 and 20, 2024, a threat actor used phishing emails to steal login credentials from 53 LA County Department of Public Health employees, gaining access to their email accounts and the personally identifiable information and PHI of over 200,000 individuals stored within those inboxes. The exposed data was among the most sensitive possible for a public health agency: names, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, diagnoses, prescriptions, medical record numbers, health insurance information, and financial data. Upon discovery, DPH disabled the compromised accounts, reset and re-imaged affected devices, blocked phishing-related websites, and quarantined suspicious incoming emails. Law enforcement was notified and conducted an investigation; affected individuals were offered one year of free credit and identity monitoring services.",
