    "title": "Palomar Health Medical Group: Network intrusion exposes patient data across multiple affiliated groups",
    "summary": "An unauthorized threat actor gained access to Palomar Health Medical Group's (Arch Health Partners / Poway, CA) network on April 23, 2024, maintaining access until detection on May 5, 2024. Compromised files contained a broad range of PHI and PII including SSNs, passport numbers, biometric data, financial accounts, payment cards, HSA information, medical histories, and treatment records for patients of Palomar Health Medical Group, Graybill Medical Group, and Pacific Accountable Care. The file review was not completed until September 2025, delaying notifications. The incident was reported to HHS OCR as affecting at least 501 individuals initially, with the final count pending full review.",
