    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "An unauthorized third party accessed Dignity Health Lassen Medical Clinic's IT network at its Red Bluff and Cottonwood, California locations between September 17 and 20, 2024, with the active cyber event detected on September 20. The network was disabled upon detection and restored the following day — a roughly 24-hour outage — but not before the attacker copied confidential patient files. Critically, no data was taken from the electronic medical record system itself; the compromised files were in other network storage. The breach exposed personal and insurance information for 65,482 patients, including names, addresses, dates of birth, driver's license numbers, financial account information, and health insurance details. The breach was disclosed to HHS OCR on December 23, 2024, and notification letters were mailed December 27, 2024.",
