    "title": "Tri-City Medical Center: Inc Ransom data disclosed, 108,149 patients notified a year later",
    "summary": "Tri-City Medical Center (Oceanside, CA), operated by Tri-City Healthcare District, suffered a ransomware attack first identified on November 9, 2023, with the Inc Ransom group claiming responsibility and posting data to its leak site in December 2023. However, Tri-City did not determine that patient data had been compromised until late September 2024, and only then mailed notification letters on October 11, 2024—nearly a year after the attack. The breach affected 108,149 individuals whose names and identifying information were exposed; the delayed notification raised potential HIPAA compliance concerns.",
