    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "In December 2023, the RansomHouse ransomware group breached Dameron Hospital in Stockton, California, exfiltrating over 480 gigabytes of data and threatening to publish it unless a ransom was paid. The group demanded payment for deletion of the stolen files; when the ransom went unpaid, data was disseminated on the dark web. The attack exposed the personal and health information of 272,475 individuals, including names, addresses, Social Security numbers, payment and financial account information, and health insurance and medical data. Dameron Hospital did not complete patient notifications until approximately 16 months after the initial attack. The hospital agreed to a $650,000 class action settlement, with California residents eligible for higher individual compensation up to $5,000 for documented losses.",
