    "summary": "Pomona Valley Hospital Medical Center (PVHMC) sent breach notification letters on March 22, 2024, informing 13,345 individuals that an unauthorized party had accessed a subcontractor's system used by one of PVHMC's business associates to store patient data. The incident involved a multi-tier vendor chain (hospital → business associate → subcontractor) with the data exposure occurring at the subcontractor level. PHI contained in the compromised patient-management data was potentially accessed. Affected individuals were offered credit monitoring services.",
