    "title": "PIH Health: Ransomware attack disrupts three SoCal hospitals, 3.3M+ records stolen",
    "summary": "Starting December 1, 2024, a ransomware attack encrypted systems across PIH Health's three Los Angeles-area hospitals (Downey, Good Samaritan, and Whittier), forcing ambulance diversions, postponed surgeries, and weeks-long outages of EHR, pharmacy, radiology, and lab systems. Hackers claimed to have stolen approximately 17 million patient records; PIH Health formally confirmed to HHS that 3,300,000+ individuals' PHI was breached and completed notification letters on February 25, 2026. At least one patient filed a class action lawsuit. The FBI was engaged, and a third-party forensic firm assisted the investigation.",
    "source_url": "https://www.beckershospitalreview.com/cybersecurity/ransomware-attack-affects-3-3-million-patients-in-california.html",
    "source_name": "Becker's Hospital Review",
    "date": "2024-12-01",
    "severity": "critical",
    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Hospital / Health System",
    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": true,
    "enriched_summary": "Starting December 1, 2024, ransomware crippled systems across PIH Health's three Los Angeles-area hospitals — Downey, Good Samaritan, and Whittier — forcing ambulance diversions, postponed surgeries, and extended outages of EHR, pharmacy, radiology, and laboratory systems that drove staff to paper-based downtime procedures for weeks. The forensic investigation, assisted by a third-party firm and the FBI, confirmed threat-actor access from November 14 through December 23, 2024. PIH Health formally confirmed to HHS that 3,300,000+ individuals' PHI was breached — though attackers separately claimed to have stolen data on 17 million patients including cancer treatment records, employee NDAs, and private patient emails. Patient notification letters were mailed February 25, 2026, over 14 months after the attack, and at least one class action lawsuit was filed.",
