    "title": "Episource (Gardena, CA): Ransomware attack exposes 5.4M patient records across Sharp HealthCare and other clients",
    "summary": "Episource, a California-based (Gardena) UnitedHealth/Optum subsidiary providing risk adjustment and coding services, suffered a ransomware attack between January 27 and February 6, 2025, in which an unauthorized actor accessed and copied data. More than 5.4 million individuals nationwide were affected, making it the second-largest healthcare breach of 2025. Among California providers directly impacted were Sharp HealthCare (24,971 individuals) and Sharp Community Medical Group (2,029 individuals), who were notified in April 2025. Exposed data included diagnoses, treatment records, medications, medical record numbers, and in some cases Social Security numbers.",
