    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": true,
    "enriched_summary": "Episource, a risk adjustment and medical coding company owned by Optum/UnitedHealth Group, suffered a ransomware attack between January 27 and February 6, 2025, in which attackers were inside the company's systems for roughly ten days before discovery. The attacker accessed and exfiltrated patient data from multiple health system clients, ultimately impacting more than 5.4 million individuals nationwide — making it the second-largest healthcare breach of 2025. Episource temporarily shut down its systems to contain the breach and began notifying affected individuals on a rolling basis starting April 23, 2025. California providers directly impacted included Sharp HealthCare and Sharp Community Medical Group.",
