    "title": "Kentfield Rehabilitation & Specialty Hospital: World Leaks cyberattack and data exfiltration",
    "summary": "In July 2025, the World Leaks threat group (believed to be a rebrand or offshoot of Hunters International) claimed a cyberattack on Kentfield Rehabilitation and Specialty Hospital in Kentfield, Marin County, California — a Long-Term Acute Care (LTAC) hospital operated by Vibra Healthcare. The attackers claimed to have exfiltrated 146.4 GB of data comprising over 140,000 files, including patient PHI such as admission, treatment, and discharge records, medical images, diagnoses, medications, test results, and quality-improvement reviews. As of July 2025, neither Kentfield nor Vibra Healthcare had publicly confirmed the breach or filed an official HHS OCR notification, though attorneys and cybersecurity researchers noted the organization faced reportable breach obligations under HIPAA.",
