    "title": "Seasons Living: Network breach exposes residents, employees across multi-state assisted living and memory care communities including California",
    "summary": "On March 4, 2025, Seasons Living — a senior living operator headquartered in Lake Oswego, Oregon, with communities across Arizona, California (including Westwind Memory Care in Santa Cruz), Idaho, Kansas, and Oregon — discovered that a cybercriminal using the alias 'f1y' had gained unauthorized access to its network and exfiltrated sensitive personal data. The breach affected vendors, rental applicants, tenants, current and former employees, and property owners, with compromised data including names, addresses, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, health insurance information, medical records, and financial data. Seasons Living published a notice on August 6, 2025, notified the California Attorney General and multiple other state AGs, and offered 12 months of complimentary credit monitoring to affected individuals. The total number of affected individuals was not publicly disclosed but was believed to be in the thousands; attorneys began investigating potential class action litigation.",
