    "title": "PIH Health Home Health & Hospice (Southern California): Ransomware attack disrupts home health, hospice, and hospital operations",
    "summary": "On December 1, 2024, PIH Health — a Southern California regional healthcare network serving Orange County and San Gabriel Valley that includes Downey Hospital, Good Samaritan Hospital, Whittier Hospital, urgent care centers, physician offices, and critically a home health and hospice agency — detected a ransomware attack. Unauthorized threat actors had access to the network from November 14 through December 23, 2024. Attackers claimed to have exfiltrated approximately 2 terabytes of data including 17 million patient records. PIH Health filed breach notifications and mailed patient notification letters in 2025 (process completed February 25, 2026 after the full affected-individual list was obtained in December 2025); the company also reached a separate $600,000 HIPAA settlement with OCR in April 2025 stemming from a prior 2019 phishing incident. The December 2024 ransomware attack disrupted home health and hospice services across Southern California.",
