    "title": "Deer Oaks – The Behavioral Health Solution: $225,000 HIPAA settlement for breaches involving long-term care and assisted living facility patients (national, includes CA facilities)",
    "summary": "On July 7, 2025, HHS OCR announced a $225,000 HIPAA settlement with Deer Oaks – The Behavioral Health Solution (San Antonio, TX), the nation's leading behavioral health provider serving residents of long-term care and assisted living facilities in 29 states including California. OCR's investigation began in May 2023 after patient discharge summaries were found publicly accessible online due to a coding error, affecting 35 individuals with PHI including names, diagnoses, and facility names. OCR expanded its investigation after a separate August 2023 ransomware incident in which a threat actor exfiltrated data and demanded payment, ultimately resulting in breach notifications to 171,871 individuals. OCR found Deer Oaks failed to conduct an adequate HIPAA risk analysis. Deer Oaks agreed to pay $225,000 and implement a two-year corrective action plan — a settlement with direct impact on California-based LTC and assisted living residents served by the company.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hhs.gov/press-room/ocr-hipaa-racap-deer-oaks.html",
