    "enriched_summary": "HHS OCR announced a $225,000 HIPAA settlement on July 7, 2025 with Deer Oaks — The Behavioral Health Solution, the nation's leading behavioral health provider serving residents of long-term care and assisted living facilities across 29 states including California. OCR's investigation originated from a May 2023 complaint after patient discharge summaries were found publicly accessible online due to a coding error affecting 35 individuals, and expanded to cover a separate August 2023 ransomware attack in which a threat actor exfiltrated data and demanded payment, ultimately resulting in breach notifications to 171,871 individuals. OCR found Deer Oaks failed to conduct an adequate HIPAA risk analysis — a fundamental Security Rule requirement — making it vulnerable to both incidents. Deer Oaks agreed to pay $225,000 and implement a two-year corrective action plan monitored by OCR.",
