    "title": "Sunshine Behavioral Health Group: AWS S3 Misconfiguration Exposes 93,000 Files on 3,500 Patients",
    "summary": "Sunshine Behavioral Health Group, LLC, a San Juan Capistrano, California-based network of drug and alcohol addiction rehabilitation centers (operating Monarch Shore, Chapters Capistrano, and Willow Springs Recovery), had an Amazon AWS S3 bucket misconfiguration that exposed over 93,000 billing files — primarily covering 3,500 patients — from March 2017 until its discovery in August 2019. Although the company was notified of the exposure in September 2019, patient notifications were not issued until January 2020 and HHS OCR was not notified until December 12, 2019. The delayed notification triggered a CCPA class action lawsuit filed on March 10, 2020 (Fuentes v. Sunshine Behavioral Health Group, Case No. 8:20-cv-00487, C.D. Cal.), with the parties reaching a settlement by August 2020.",
