    "title": "Cerebral Inc: HIPAA Breach Exposes Mental Health Data of 3.1 Million Users via Advertising Pixels",
    "summary": "San Francisco-based telemental health startup Cerebral Inc. disclosed on March 6, 2023 that it had violated HIPAA by sharing the protected health information of 3,179,835 patients with Facebook, Google, TikTok, and other third-party advertising platforms via embedded tracking pixels active from October 2019 through January 3, 2023. Exposed data included names, phone numbers, email addresses, dates of birth, IP addresses, mental health self-assessment responses, appointment dates, treatment details, and health insurance information. The FTC subsequently fined Cerebral $7 million in April 2024 for the privacy violations, making it the second-largest health data breach of 2023 and a landmark enforcement action against a mental health telehealth provider.",
