    "summary": "Turning Point of Central California, a nonprofit providing mental health, addiction recovery, children's services, and housing programs, had its network compromised beginning January 30, 2024, with unauthorized access persisting until June 18, 2024. The Abyss ransomware group claimed responsibility and alleged exfiltration of 570 GB of data including names, Social Security numbers, and addresses of clients and employees. The breach was reported to HHS OCR on August 9, 2024, with affected individuals notified starting August 30, 2024.",
