    "title": "Omni Family Health: Ransomware Attack Exposes 468,000 Behavioral Health and Primary Care Patients",
    "summary": "Omni Family Health, a California nonprofit operating approximately 40 community health centers in Kern, Kings, Tulare, and Fresno counties offering behavioral health among other services, discovered a ransomware attack on August 7, 2024. The Hunters International ransomware group claimed responsibility, alleging theft of 2.7 terabytes of data and leaking it on August 23, 2024. Approximately 468,344 individuals had records exposed including names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, health insurance, and medical information; Omni Family Health agreed to a $6.5 million class action settlement.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hipaajournal.com/data-breach-omni-family-health-signature-healthcare-services/",
    "source_name": "HIPAA Journal",
