    "title": "American Addiction Centers: Rhysida Ransomware Attack Affects 422,000 Substance Abuse Treatment Patients Including California",
    "summary": "American Addiction Centers, which operates addiction rehabilitation facilities across California and other states, was attacked by the Rhysida ransomware group between September 23-26, 2024. Rhysida published 2.8 terabytes of stolen data after the ransom went unpaid, exposing names, addresses, phone numbers, medical record numbers, Social Security numbers, and health insurance information for approximately 422,424 individuals. The company mailed breach notifications in December 2024 and later agreed to a $2.75 million settlement.",
