    "org_type": "Mental Health / Behavioral Health",
    "healthcare_sector": "Behavioral Health",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between September 23-26, 2024, the Rhysida ransomware group attacked American Addiction Centers, a national network of addiction rehabilitation facilities with locations across California, Florida, Texas, Nevada, and other states. The breach was discovered September 26, 2024, with the Rhysida gang publicly claiming responsibility on November 16, 2024, after AAC declined to pay the ransom and 2.8 terabytes of stolen data was published. Approximately 422,424 patients were affected, with notification letters mailed before Christmas 2024. American Addiction Centers agreed to a $2.75 million class action settlement with a final fairness hearing scheduled for April 2026; class members are eligible for up to $5,000 in documented loss reimbursement plus approximately $50 in pro rata cash payments.",
