    "summary": "Between January 15 and February 3, 2025, an unauthorized actor accessed an employee email account at Hope Cooperative, a Sacramento-based nonprofit providing behavioral health and supportive housing services to individuals in Sacramento and Yolo County for over 40 years. The organization discovered the suspicious activity on February 3, 2025 and notified attorneys general in eleven states. Potentially exposed data included names, Social Security numbers, addresses, dates of birth, driver's license numbers, financial account information, and medical/insurance data belonging to vulnerable mental health and substance use disorder patients.",
