    "enriched_summary": "Between January 15 and February 3, 2025, an unauthorized actor gained access to an employee email account at Hope Cooperative (TLCS Inc.), a Sacramento-based nonprofit serving behavioral health and supportive housing clients in Sacramento and Yolo County for over 40 years. The organization discovered the suspicious activity on February 3, 2025, and immediately engaged third-party incident response and forensic specialists to investigate. The email account contained highly sensitive protected health information for mental health patients, including psychiatric diagnoses, medication details, substance use treatment information, and crisis intervention history. Hope Cooperative filed breach notifications with attorneys general in eleven states, indicating the breach affected individuals across multiple jurisdictions.",
