    "summary": "American Addiction Centers, the largest US addiction treatment provider, suffered a Rhysida ransomware attack between September 23-26, 2024, which was discovered on September 26, 2024 and confirmed on October 3, 2024. Approximately 410,747–422,424 patients were affected nationwide, including those at Laguna Treatment Hospital in Laguna Beach, California. The attackers leaked 2.8 TB of data after AAC declined to pay the ransom. Notification letters went out November–December 2024, and a $2.75 million class action settlement received preliminary court approval on December 5, 2025, covering approximately 423,064 class members. Exposed data included names, addresses, phone numbers, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, medical record numbers, and health insurance details.",
