    "org_type": "Mental Health / Behavioral Health",
    "healthcare_sector": "Behavioral Health",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Gardner Health Services, a San Jose, California Federally Qualified Health Center, was one of numerous healthcare providers affected when their billing vendor, TriZetto Provider Solutions (a Cognizant subsidiary), suffered a breach of its web portal. Unauthorized access to TriZetto's systems began in November 2024 but was not detected until October 2, 2025. TriZetto notified Gardner Health on December 9, 2025, and Gardner Health mailed breach notification letters to approximately 26,000 affected patients on December 22, 2025. The overall TriZetto breach exposed data belonging to 3,433,965 individuals across multiple healthcare clients nationwide. Exposed data included names, addresses, birthdates, Social Security numbers, and health insurance member numbers.",
