    "title": "California Health & Wellness: Accellion FTA Breach Exposes 80,138 Medi-Cal Members",
    "summary": "California Health & Wellness (CHW), a Centene-owned Medi-Cal managed care plan operating in California, was notified on January 25, 2021 that its data stored on Accellion's File Transfer Appliance had been accessed by unauthorized actors between January 7 and January 25, 2021. The breach exposed the names, addresses, dates of birth, insurance ID numbers, and health information of 80,138 plan members. CHW ceased using Accellion's services, coordinated with law enforcement including the FBI, and offered one year of complimentary credit monitoring to affected members. CHW was included in the broader Centene/Health Net $10 million class action settlement.",
