    "enriched_summary": "California Health & Wellness (CHW), a Centene-owned Medi-Cal managed care plan, was notified on January 25, 2021 that data it had stored on Accellion's File Transfer Appliance had been accessed by unauthorized actors between January 7 and January 25, 2021, as part of the broader FIN11/Clop-linked zero-day exploitation campaign targeting Accellion's legacy FTA platform. The breach exposed the records of 80,138 CHW plan members including names, addresses, dates of birth, insurance ID numbers, and health information. CHW immediately ceased using Accellion's services, coordinated with law enforcement including the FBI, and publicly announced the breach on March 24, 2021. CHW was included in the broader Centene/Health Net $10 million class action settlement.",
