    "title": "CalViva Health: Accellion FTA Breach Affects Fresno-Area Medi-Cal Members",
    "summary": "CalViva Health, a locally managed public Medi-Cal managed care plan based in Fresno, California, was affected by the same January 2021 Accellion FTA zero-day exploitation campaign that struck multiple California health plans. Accellion notified CalViva on January 25, 2021 that unauthorized actors had accessed its data files via the FTA platform between January 7 and January 25. CalViva's member data was hosted through its vendor Health Net Community Solutions and managed on Accellion's platform. The organization notified affected members by mail on March 26, 2021, ceased using Accellion, and offered one year of credit monitoring and identity theft protection services. HHS OCR breach filings list approximately 15,287 records affected.",
