    "title": "Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan: OneTouchPoint Vendor Ransomware Breach Exposes Member PHI",
    "summary": "On April 27, 2022, OneTouchPoint (OTP), a printing and mailing vendor used by Matrix Medical Network (a contractor to Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan), suffered a ransomware attack that encrypted files on its servers. The breach was discovered April 28, 2022, and Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan was notified on June 16, 2022. Approximately 1,506 Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan members had their names, subscriber IDs, diagnoses, medications, addresses, dates of birth, physician demographics, family and social histories, allergies, vitals, and immunizations exposed.",
