    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Health Insurance / Payer",
    "healthcare_sector": "Payer / Insurance",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "In April 2022, OneTouchPoint (OTP), a printing and mailing vendor used by Matrix Medical Network on behalf of Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan, was hit with ransomware that encrypted files on its servers. The breach was discovered April 28, 2022, but it took over a month before OTP could even determine what specific files the unauthorized actor had viewed. At least 34 healthcare organizations were ultimately notified of exposure through OTP, with Blue Shield of California Promise Health Plan members receiving notice in June 2022. OTP did not provide identity theft protection services to victims and did not respond to media inquiries.",
