    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "The Clop ransomware group exploited a zero-day vulnerability in Fortra's GoAnywhere MFT file transfer solution on or around January 30, 2023, compromising data flowing through NationsBenefits, a supplemental benefits vendor serving Santa Clara Family Health Plan (SCFHP). NationsBenefits learned of the attack on February 7, 2023 and immediately took its GoAnywhere server permanently offline, replacing it with a Microsoft Azure-based SFTP solution. The attack affected 130 organizations over a 10-day period; SCFHP reported the breach to HHS OCR on March 30, 2023, affecting 276,993 Medicaid managed care plan members serving low-income residents of Santa Clara County. A $20 million multidistrict litigation settlement was reached to resolve Fortra GoAnywhere-related lawsuits.",
