    "title": "Prospect Medical Holdings: Rhysida Ransomware Disrupts California Hospitals and Exposes 1.3 Million Records",
    "summary": "On August 3, 2023, the Rhysida ransomware group attacked Prospect Medical Holdings, a Los Angeles-based healthcare system operating seven hospitals in California (including Southern California hospitals). The attack forced emergency room closures and ambulance diversions, with facilities reverting to paper records for several weeks. Rhysida claimed to have stolen 500,000 Social Security numbers and extensive patient records; the confirmed breach ultimately affected approximately 1.3 million individuals. Exposed data included names, SSNs, dates of birth, financial information, diagnoses, lab results, and health insurance information.",
    "source_url": "https://therecord.media/prospect-hospitals-still-recovering",
    "source_name": "The Record / Recorded Future News",
    "date": "2023-08-03",
    "severity": "critical",
    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Health Insurance / Payer",
    "healthcare_sector": "Payer / Insurance",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On August 3, 2023, the Rhysida ransomware group — which had only emerged in May 2023 and was believed to have connections to the Vice Society group — attacked Prospect Medical Holdings, a Los Angeles-based system operating 16 facilities across California, Rhode Island, Connecticut, and Pennsylvania. The attack forced ambulance diversions, appointment cancellations, and clinic closures, with staff reverting to paper records for patient care. Emergency departments and outpatient diagnostic services including imaging and blood draws were disrupted; hospital leadership stated they did not know when systems would be restored. Rhysida threatened to leak stolen data unless a ransom was paid, and the confirmed breach ultimately affected approximately 1.3 million individuals.",
