    "title": "Keenan & Associates: Cyberattack on California Insurance Broker Exposes Health Data of 1.5 Million",
    "summary": "Between August 21 and August 27, 2023, an unauthorized actor accessed systems at Keenan & Associates, a California-based insurance brokerage and benefits consulting firm that administers health, workers' compensation, and employee benefits plans for organizations across California. Approximately 1,573,844 individuals had their data exposed, including names, dates of birth, SSNs, passport numbers, driver's license numbers, health insurance information, and medical information. A $14 million class action settlement was reached, with California residents eligible for higher payouts than other states.",
