    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between August 21 and August 27, 2023, an unauthorized actor accessed systems at Keenan & Associates, a California-based insurance brokerage and benefits consulting firm that administers health, workers' compensation, and employee benefits plans for organizations across California. Approximately 1,573,844 individuals had their sensitive personal and health data exposed, including Social Security numbers, passport numbers, driver's license numbers, and medical and health insurance information. Multiple class action lawsuits were consolidated and settled for $14 million, with class members eligible for three years of credit monitoring services and cash payments of up to $10,000 for documented fraud losses.",
