    "title": "Covered California: Health Insurance Exchange Transmitted Sensitive Member Data to LinkedIn via Trackers",
    "summary": "Beginning in February 2024, Covered California — California's ACA health insurance marketplace — ran an advertising campaign that embedded LinkedIn Insight Tags and other trackers on its website, inadvertently transmitting sensitive health information of visitors to LinkedIn. Data shared included first names, last four digits of Social Security numbers, pregnancy status, disability status, and other health conditions entered into enrollment forms. The trackers were removed in early April 2024; a proposed class-action lawsuit was filed and federal lawmakers called on HHS to investigate potential HIPAA violations.",
