    "state": "CA",
    "org_type": "Health Insurance / Payer",
    "healthcare_sector": "Payer / Insurance",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Beginning in February 2024, Covered California — California's ACA health insurance marketplace — ran an advertising campaign that embedded LinkedIn Insight Tags on its website, inadvertently transmitting sensitive health information of visitors to LinkedIn. The trackers captured users' answers to enrollment questions about pregnancy, blindness, high prescription use, gender identity, and domestic abuse experiences, along with names and partial Social Security numbers. The trackers were removed in early April 2024 following a marketing agency transition. A proposed class-action lawsuit was filed against LinkedIn and Google one day after a CalMatters/The Markup investigation, and House lawmakers wrote to HHS asking whether the practice violated HIPAA.",
