    "title": "TriZetto Provider Solutions: 3.4 Million Records Stolen in 2024 Hack Affecting California Health Clinics",
    "summary": "Beginning in November 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed TriZetto Provider Solutions' web portal and stole insurance eligibility verification records for 3.4 million individuals; the breach went undetected for nearly a year until October 2025. Among the affected California organizations were Gardner Health Services (San Jose) and San Francisco Community Health Center, whose patient eligibility and insurance records were compromised. Stolen data included names, dates of birth, addresses, Social Security numbers, provider names, and health and insurance details; TriZetto filed breach notifications in California and multiple other states.",
