    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Beginning in November 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed TriZetto Provider Solutions' web portal — a Cognizant subsidiary that processes insurance claims and eligibility verification for over 4 billion transactions annually — and stole insurance eligibility verification records for approximately 3.4 million individuals. The breach went undetected for nearly 11 months until October 2025, when Mandiant (a Google-owned cybersecurity firm) conducted the investigation. Among the California organizations affected were Gardner Health Services (San Jose) and San Francisco Community Health Center. TriZetto began notifying customers in December 2025; neither TriZetto nor parent company Cognizant responded to media requests for comment.",
