    "title": "Blue Shield of California: Conduent Third-Party Ransomware Breach — Member PII/PHI Exposed",
    "summary": "On January 13, 2025, Blue Shield of California's vendor Conduent Business Services (a back-office services provider) discovered an intrusion by the SafePay ransomware group that had persisted from October 21, 2024 to January 13, 2025. Conduent notified Blue Shield on November 6, 2025 that Blue Shield member PHI was in the exfiltrated files. Exposed data for Blue Shield members included names, dates of birth, addresses, Social Security Numbers, treatment/diagnosis codes, provider names, dates of service, claim amounts, group numbers, and subscriber IDs. Blue Shield publicly notified members on February 24, 2026. The Conduent breach grew to affect more than 25 million individuals across multiple health plan clients nationwide, representing one of the largest healthcare data breaches in U.S. history.",
    "source_url": "https://news.blueshieldca.com/february-24-2026-blue-shield-of-california-notifies-members-of-third-party-potential-privacy-breach",
