    "enriched_summary": "On January 13, 2025, Blue Shield of California's vendor Conduent Business Services discovered that the SafePay ransomware group had maintained unauthorized access to its environment from October 21, 2024 through January 13, 2025, exfiltrating approximately 8.5 terabytes of data. Conduent did not notify Blue Shield that Blue Shield member PHI was among the stolen files until November 6, 2025 — nearly 10 months after containment. Blue Shield publicly notified affected members on February 24, 2026. The Conduent breach expanded to affect over 25 million individuals across multiple health plan clients including Anthem Blue Cross Blue Shield affiliates, Humana, and Premera, representing one of the largest healthcare data breaches in U.S. history.",
