    "title": "PIH Health (California Health Care Network): $600,000 HHS OCR HIPAA Settlement for 2019 Phishing Breach",
    "summary": "On April 23, 2025, HHS Office for Civil Rights announced a $600,000 HIPAA settlement with PIH Health, Inc., a California integrated health care network serving Los Angeles and Orange counties. The settlement stemmed from a June 2019 phishing attack that compromised 45 employee email accounts and exposed the ePHI of 189,763 individuals, including names, addresses, SSNs, DOBs, diagnoses, lab results, medications, and financial information. OCR found failures in risk analysis, risk management, and impermissible PHI disclosure. PIH agreed to a $600,000 payment and a two-year corrective action plan monitored by OCR. Note: PIH Health is primarily a provider network but administers health plan benefits, making it a HIPAA covered entity on the payer side.",
