    "title": "Kroger Pharmacy: Accellion Third-Party Breach Exposes 1.47 Million Pharmacy Records",
    "summary": "Kroger was notified on January 23, 2021, that its use of the Accellion File Transfer Appliance had been compromised by the CLOP ransomware group, exposing the pharmacy and HR records of approximately 1,474,284 customers and employees, including those served by Kroger's California pharmacy locations. Kroger received a ransom demand on February 2, 2021. Exposed pharmacy data included prescription information and health-related records. A California federal judge (N.D. Cal.) preliminarily approved Kroger's $5 million settlement, and the incident was part of a broader Accellion FTA supply-chain attack that affected multiple healthcare organizations.",
