    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "In December 2020, the CLOP ransomware group exploited zero-day vulnerabilities in Accellion's File Transfer Appliance (FTA), a service Kroger used for secure file transfers. Kroger was notified of the breach on January 23, 2021, and immediately discontinued use of the Accellion FTA. Stolen data included pharmacy records, HR data, and money services records for over 3.8 million individuals; CLOP threatened to publicly release stolen data unless a ransom was paid. Kroger proposed a $5 million class action settlement that required dark web monitoring for five years, destruction of stolen data, and an enhanced vendor risk management program.",
