    "enriched_summary": "Between August 6 and 8, 2024, INC Ransom — a ransomware-as-a-service group that employs double extortion tactics — infiltrated the systems of OnePoint Patient Care, a national hospice and palliative care-focused specialty pharmacy headquartered in Tempe, AZ. The company discovered the intrusion on August 15, 2024, after engaging third-party cybersecurity experts, who confirmed that files containing patient PHI had been exfiltrated without authorization. Although OPPC's pharmacy operations reportedly continued without major disruption, the company notified HHS OCR on October 14 with an initial count of 795,916 affected individuals, which was revised sharply upward to 1,741,152 on November 22, 2024, after further investigation. INC Ransom ultimately published the stolen data on its dark web leak site after ransom payment was not made to prevent disclosure, and multiple class action lawsuits were filed alleging negligence in network security.",
