    "title": "Sav-Rx (A&A Services): PBM Network Breach Notified 2.8 Million Including California Members in 2024",
    "summary": "Sav-Rx, a Nebraska-based pharmacy benefit management company, disclosed in May 2024 that hackers accessed its network in October 2023 and exfiltrated protected health information; the breach was not discovered until October 2023 but individual notifications to the 2,812,336 affected individuals — which included California health plan members — did not begin until late May 2024. The compromised data included names, dates of birth, email addresses, phone numbers, physical addresses, insurance member ID numbers, and health plan information. Sav-Rx reported the breach to HHS OCR and claimed the stolen data was permanently deleted and not further disseminated.",
