    "title": "South Lake Tahoe Pharmacies (Tahoe Valley Pharmacy, Safeway): Change Healthcare Outage Disrupts Operations",
    "summary": "Multiple pharmacies in South Lake Tahoe, California — including Tahoe Valley Pharmacy and two Safeway pharmacy locations — experienced significant operational disruptions beginning February 21, 2024, as a result of the Change Healthcare ransomware attack. Pharmacies were unable to bill insurance, verify eligibility, or receive electronic prescriptions for multiple days, forcing manual workarounds; Tahoe Valley Pharmacy owner Doug Mundy confirmed no patient PHI at the local pharmacy was directly compromised. The disruption was attributed entirely to the ALPHV/BlackCat attack on Change Healthcare's clearinghouse systems.",
