    "healthcare_sector": "Pharmacy",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Beginning February 21, 2024, multiple pharmacies in South Lake Tahoe, California — including Tahoe Valley Pharmacy and two Safeway locations at Elks Point in Stateline, NV and Johnson Way — were operationally paralyzed by the downstream effects of the ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware attack on Change Healthcare's clearinghouse systems. Pharmacies could not bill insurance, verify patient eligibility, or receive electronic prescriptions, forcing manual workarounds including converting prescriptions to maintain data security. By the time the local article published on March 4, 2024, Tahoe Valley Pharmacy reported operations had largely returned to normal aside from a few residual issues that could not be specified for security reasons. No patient protected health information at the local pharmacies was directly compromised — the exposure was entirely operational, not a data breach of local systems.",
