    "title": "Episource (UnitedHealth/Optum, Los Angeles CA): Ransomware exposes 5.4 million patients including prescription and diagnosis data",
    "summary": "California-based Episource LLC, an Optum/UnitedHealth subsidiary providing medical coding and risk-adjustment services, suffered a ransomware-driven data theft between January 27 and February 6, 2025. Hackers exfiltrated data on 5,418,866 individuals, including names, contact details, Social Security numbers, health insurance IDs, Medicaid/Medicare IDs, diagnosis information, treatment records, prescriptions, test results, and medical images. Sharp HealthCare (24,971 affected) and Sharp Community Medical Group (2,029 affected) confirmed impact among California-based provider clients. Episource notified HHS OCR on behalf of affected clients and filed with the California Attorney General on June 6, 2025; the breach made it the second-largest healthcare data breach reported to HHS in 2025.",
