    "healthcare_sector": "Pharmacy",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between February 4 and February 7, 2026, the ShinyHunters extortion gang used social engineering — impersonating IT support and tricking employees into entering credentials and MFA codes on phishing pages — to compromise Okta SSO accounts at Hims & Hers, a San Francisco-based telehealth pharmacy with approximately 2.5 million subscribers. With SSO access, the attackers reached the company's Zendesk customer support platform and acquired millions of support tickets containing customer names and contact information. Medical records, prescription data, and communications with healthcare providers were confirmed not to have been accessed. Hims & Hers notified the California Attorney General on April 2, 2026, is sending individual breach notifications, and is offering 12 months of free credit monitoring; class action investigations were launched by multiple law firms including Edelson Lechtzin LLP.",
