    "title": "Sea Mar Community Health Centers Data Exfiltration Breach — 688,000 Patients Affected",
    "summary": "Sea Mar Community Health Centers, one of the nation's largest Federally Qualified Health Centers (FQHCs) serving diverse and Latino communities across Washington state with over 90 clinic sites providing medical, dental, and behavioral health services, suffered a major data theft. Threat actors accessed Sea Mar's digital environment and copied patient data between approximately December 2020 and March 2021. Sea Mar was informed by the Marketo cybercrime group on June 24, 2021 that stolen data was being offered for sale on the dark web; the group continued listing the data through November 10, 2021. Sea Mar completed its review of affected individuals by August 30, 2021 and began notifying over 688,000 current and former patients in October 2021 — approximately four months after discovery. Exposed data included names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, client identification numbers, medical/vision/dental/orthodontic diagnostic and treatment information, insurance information, claims data, and dental treatment images. A $4.4 million class-action settlement was upheld by the Washington Court of Appeals in January 2024.",
