    "summary": "Woodcreek Provider Services LLC, a medical practice management company in Puyallup, Washington that supports pediatric clinics and urgent care centers affiliated with MultiCare Health System, disclosed a data breach resulting from a ransomware attack on its cloud IT hosting vendor, Netgain Technology LLC. Attackers compromised Netgain's systems between approximately November 24 and December 3, 2020 (with possible access since September 2020) and exfiltrated an archive server containing clinical and financial records. Woodcreek received confirmation of what data was involved on January 18, 2021, after paying a ransom. Woodcreek notified the Washington Attorney General on February 17, 2021 and reported to HHS OCR on March 5, 2021 as affecting approximately 207,000 individuals; a second group of approximately 210,000 additional individuals also received HIPAA notifications. Exposed data included names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, medical record numbers, health insurance information, clinical notes, referral requests, lab reports, immunization records, prescription requests, bank account numbers, payroll records, and court documents.",
