    "enriched_summary": "Woodcreek Provider Services LLC, a medical practice management company in Puyallup, WA supporting pediatric clinics and urgent care centers affiliated with MultiCare Health System, was compromised through its cloud IT hosting vendor Netgain Technology LLC. Attackers breached Netgain’s infrastructure between approximately November 24 and December 3, 2020 (with possible initial access as early as September 2020) and exfiltrated an archive server containing clinical and financial records including SSNs, medical record numbers, immunization records, bank account numbers, and payroll records. Woodcreek received confirmation of the exposed data on January 18, 2021 after paying a ransom to Netgain, then filed separate notifications with the Washington Attorney General on February 17, 2021 and HHS OCR on March 5, 2021. A second group of approximately 210,000 additional individuals also received HIPAA notifications, bringing the total potential impact to over 400,000 individuals.",
