    "title": "Western Washington Medical Group Hit by Play Ransomware, 350,863 Patients Affected",
    "summary": "On August 26, 2023, Western Washington Medical Group — a multi-specialty physician group of more than 100 providers serving Snohomish, Skagit, Island, and Whatcom counties — detected unauthorized access to its network, believed to have originated from a phishing email. The organization immediately shut off network access and engaged a third-party cybersecurity firm. The breach was reported to HHS OCR on October 26, 2023, and patient notification letters were sent November 6, 2023. On October 28, 2023, the Play ransomware hacking group claimed responsibility for the attack. Exposed data varied by individual and may have included names, addresses, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, medical record numbers, health insurance policy numbers, medical history, diagnoses, and treatment information. No evidence of actual data misuse was found at time of notification; affected individuals were offered 12 months of complimentary credit monitoring.",
