    "enriched_summary": "MultiCare Health System, Washington’s largest locally-owned nonprofit health system headquartered in Tacoma, had over 200,000 patient and staff records exposed through a ransomware attack on its third-party IT vendor Netgain Technology LLC, which hosted the network for Woodcreek Provider Services. Attackers deployed ransomware on December 3, 2020, after gaining initial access as early as September 2020, and exfiltrated a Woodcreek archive server containing clinical and financial PHI dating back to 2005. A ransom was paid and data recovered by January 18, 2021; MultiCare’s primary EHR system was not directly impacted. Approximately 210,000 affected individuals — including patients, providers, and staff — were notified beginning in March 2021 after a forensic investigation confirmed the scope.",
