    "title": "Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center: Ransomware Attack by Hunters International Exposes 1.84 Million Patient Records",
    "summary": "Between November 19-25, 2023, the Hunters International ransomware gang exploited the CitrixBleed vulnerability (CVE-2023-4966) to breach Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center's clinical network in Seattle, stealing 533 GB of data including names, Social Security numbers, medical histories, lab results, and insurance information. The attackers engaged in aggressive double-extortion tactics, directly emailing patients with threats to 'swat' them unless they paid $50 individually. Fred Hutch reported the breach to HHS OCR as affecting up to 1,840,927 individuals and ultimately agreed to a class action settlement of approximately $52.5 million.",
    "source_url": "https://therecord.media/seattle-fred-hutch-cancer-center-ransomware-attack",
    "source_name": "The Record (Recorded Future News)",
    "date": "2023-11-19",
