    "state": "WA",
    "org_type": "Hospital / Health System",
    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between November 19 and 25, 2023, the Hunters International ransomware gang exploited the CitrixBleed vulnerability (CVE-2023-4966) to breach Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center’s clinical network in Seattle, stealing 533 GB of sensitive data including medical histories, lab results, and Social Security numbers. The clinical network was taken offline on December 1, 2023, while patient clinics remained open; Hunters International listed Fred Hutch on its leak site on December 15, 2023. In a highly unusual double-extortion campaign, the gang directly emailed individual cancer patients threatening to “swat” them and demanding $50 per person to remove their records from public exposure. Fred Hutch reported the breach as affecting up to 1,840,927 individuals and ultimately agreed to a class action settlement of approximately $52.5 million.",
