    "summary": "On February 21, 2024, the ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware group attacked Change Healthcare, a UnitedHealth Group subsidiary that processes a large share of U.S. prescriptions and insurance transactions. Washington state hospitals, including Providence and MultiCare facilities, experienced significant pharmacy service disruptions, delayed prior authorizations, and major payment processing outages. Washington Insurance Commissioner Mike Kreidler issued a Technical Assistance Advisory requiring health insurers to ensure compliance given the disruption, and Washington hospitals collectively lost nearly $400 million in the first nine months of 2024 partly attributable to the attack's financial fallout.",
    "source_url": "https://www.insurance.wa.gov/about-us/news/2024/after-change-healthcare-breach-kreidler-alerts-industry-their-obligations",
    "source_name": "Washington State Office of the Insurance Commissioner",
