    "title": "East Adams Rural Healthcare: Patient Data Breached in Network Intrusion",
    "summary": "East Adams Rural Healthcare, a critical access hospital in Ritzville, Washington, detected anomalous network activity on or about September 12, 2024, with the investigation later confirming unauthorized access occurred between September 7 and September 13, 2024. The breach exposed names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurance information, and medical information of at least 8,896 Washington residents. The incident was disclosed to the Washington Attorney General and affected individuals were notified in 2025.",
    "source_url": "https://www.earh.org/notice-regarding-data-security-incident-east-adams-rural-health",
