    "healthcare_sector": "Acute Care",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "East Adams Rural Healthcare (EARH), a 20-bed critical access hospital in Ritzville, Washington, detected anomalous network activity on September 12, 2024, with forensic investigation confirming unauthorized access between September 7 and September 13, 2024. Third-party cybersecurity experts were engaged to contain the affected systems and conduct a full investigation. The investigation was completed July 17, 2025, and EARH filed a breach notice with the Washington Attorney General on August 11, 2025, reporting at least 8,896 Washington residents affected. Exposed data included names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurance information, and medical records. A 2024 audit separately revealed a $10.5 million operating loss at EARH, underscoring the financial fragility of this rural critical access facility.",
