    "title": "Laboratory Services Cooperative: Hacking Incident Exposes Data of 1.6 Million People",
    "summary": "Laboratory Services Cooperative (LSC), a Seattle, WA-based nonprofit providing diagnostic lab testing services to Planned Parenthood centers in 30 states, identified unauthorized access to its computer network on October 27, 2024. An unauthorized third party exfiltrated a broad range of sensitive data including names, Social Security numbers, diagnoses, lab results, treatment information, dates of birth, and in some cases bank account and payment card details, affecting approximately 1.6 million individuals. At least three class action lawsuits were filed in the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Washington following the breach.",
