    "title": "Mt. Baker Imaging / Northwest Radiologists: Data theft exposes 348,000 patient records",
    "summary": "Between January 20-25, 2025, hackers accessed and stole sensitive patient data from Mt. Baker Imaging and its affiliated group Northwest Radiologists, which operates six facilities throughout Whatcom County in Bellingham, Washington. Stolen data included names, addresses, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, banking information, email addresses, health insurance details, and treatment information. The company waited nearly 10 months before mailing notification letters to affected patients in late October/early November 2025, drawing criticism and prompting a class action lawsuit filed in Whatcom County Superior Court in April 2025.",
