    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Between January 20 and 25, 2025, hackers accessed and stole sensitive patient data from Mt. Baker Imaging and its affiliated group Northwest Radiologists, which operates six diagnostic imaging facilities throughout Whatcom County in Bellingham, Washington. Stolen data included names, addresses, SSNs, driver’s license numbers, banking information, email addresses, health insurance details, and treatment and diagnostic information for over 348,000 patients. The company did not publicly disclose the breach until July 2025, and notification letters were not mailed to affected patients until late October/early November 2025 — nearly 10 months after the incident — drawing sharp criticism and prompting a class action lawsuit filed in Whatcom County Superior Court in April 2025.",
