    "title": "Lake Washington Vascular: Qilin ransomware attack affects 21,534 patients",
    "summary": "On February 14, 2025, the Qilin ransomware group attacked Lake Washington Vascular, a surgical vascular center in Bellevue, Washington, encrypting its electronic health record and practice management systems. The facility's IT team stopped the attack and restored data from secure off-site backups without paying the ransom. An investigation confirmed 21,534 patients had personal and health information potentially compromised, including names, birth dates, addresses, government-issued IDs, diagnostic test results, and treatment details; notification letters were mailed March 14, 2025.",
    "source_url": "https://www.hipaajournal.com/lake-washington-vascular-ransomware-attack/",
