    "date": "2025-02-14",
    "severity": "high",
    "state": "WA",
    "org_type": "Hospital / Health System",
    "healthcare_sector": "Surgical / Outpatient Specialty",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "At approximately 5:00 a.m. on February 14, 2025, the Qilin ransomware group attacked Lake Washington Vascular, a surgical vascular center in Bellevue, Washington, encrypting both its electronic health record system and practice management software. The facility’s IT team rapidly detected and stopped the attack, and the organization was able to fully restore data from secure off-site backups without paying the ransom demand. A forensic investigation confirmed 21,534 patients had personal and health information potentially compromised, including names, birth dates, addresses, government-issued IDs, diagnostic test results, and treatment details. Notification letters were mailed to affected patients on March 14, 2025.",
