    "summary": "On February 23, 2025, Klickitat Valley Health (KVH) in Goldendale, Washington detected unusual activity in its IT systems; an investigation determined an unauthorized actor had copied files from its network on February 18, 2025. The Kraken ransomware gang claimed responsibility and alleged it stole Social Security numbers and protected health information, though KVH has not confirmed this claim. KVH notified 531 individuals whose data may have included names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurance information, medical record numbers, and diagnosis and treatment details.",
