    "enriched_summary": "On February 23, 2025, Klickitat Valley Health (KVH), a rural hospital in Goldendale, Washington serving more than 5,000 residents of eastern Klickitat County, detected unusual activity in its IT systems. Investigation determined that an unauthorized actor had copied files from its network on February 18, 2025. The Kraken ransomware group, believed to be a rebranding of the HelloKitty/HelloGookie operation that emerged in February 2025, claimed responsibility and alleged theft of SSNs and protected health information, though KVH did not confirm the gang’s specific claims. KVH notified 531 individuals whose potentially exposed information included names, addresses, dates of birth, SSNs, health insurance details, medical record numbers, patient account numbers, and treatment information.",
