    "title": "DaVita: Interlock ransomware attack disrupts Whatcom County dialysis facilities, 2.7M affected nationally",
    "summary": "DaVita, the national kidney dialysis provider, suffered a ransomware attack discovered on April 12, 2025 (with initial access traced to March 24, 2025), which encrypted portions of its network including at three Whatcom County, Washington facilities in Bellingham, Ferndale, and Burlington. The Interlock ransomware group claimed responsibility and alleged theft of over 20 TB of data. DaVita confirmed 2,689,826 individuals were ultimately affected nationally, with approximately 13,404 Washington residents impacted; exposed data included names, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, dates of birth, health insurance IDs, and dialysis treatment records.",
