    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "The Interlock ransomware group first gained access to DaVita’s network on March 24, 2025, remaining undetected until DaVita’s security team identified the intrusion on April 12, 2025. The attack encrypted portions of DaVita’s network, including systems supporting at least three Whatcom County, Washington facilities in Bellingham, Ferndale, and Burlington. Interlock claimed theft of over 20 TB of data including more than 200 million rows of patient records from DaVita’s dialysis labs database. DaVita confirmed 2,689,826 individuals were ultimately affected nationally, including approximately 13,404 Washington residents. Despite the attack, DaVita reported that critical dialysis care continued uninterrupted; the company reported approximately $13.5 million in incident-related costs in Q2 2025.",
