    "title": "Avalon Health Care Management – Phishing Breach Notifies Washington Residents in Early 2020",
    "summary": "In July 2019, an employee at Avalon Health Care Management responded to a phishing email and disclosed credentials that allowed an unauthorized actor to access a corporate email account. Avalon became aware of the incident on December 16, 2019, and determined by January 27, 2020 that 1,723 Washington state residents had their names and Social Security numbers exposed, and an additional 138 Washington residents had their names and limited medical information exposed. Avalon Health Care operates skilled nursing and long-term care facilities across Washington state (including locations in Federal Way, Pasco, Tacoma, and Northpointe). The full breach affected multiple states. Avalon notified affected individuals approximately 10 months after the incident. Oregon and Utah attorneys general reached a $200,000 settlement with Avalon Healthcare Management over the breach.",
