    "title": "Avamere Health Services Ransomware Attack Affects Washington State Skilled Nursing and Senior Living Facilities",
    "summary": "Between January 19 and March 17, 2022, an unauthorized individual — believed to be a ransomware threat actor — gained access to a third-party-hosted network operated by Avamere Health Services LLC, a Wilsonville, OR-based operator of skilled nursing, rehabilitation, and senior living facilities. The attack affected 96 senior living and healthcare facilities across Oregon, Washington, Nevada, Utah, Colorado, and Arizona. Washington state facilities confirmed as impacted include Avamere at Port Townsend, Avamere Heritage Rehabilitation of Tacoma, and Richmond Beach Rehab (Shoreline). Avamere reported the breach to HHS OCR as affecting 197,730 individuals; however, additional affiliated companies, including Infinity Rehab, raised the total affected count to at least 380,984 individuals. Stolen data included names, dates of birth, addresses, Social Security numbers, lab results, medical condition information, and medication records. Avamere began notifying individuals in mid-June 2022 and offered complimentary credit monitoring. A class action lawsuit was subsequently filed in Oregon federal court.",
