    "org_type": "Mental Health / Behavioral Health",
    "healthcare_sector": "Behavioral Health",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On April 6, 2020, a threat actor sent a spear-phishing email impersonating a Magellan Health client, tricking an employee into disclosing credentials and granting access to a corporate server. By April 11, 2020, Magellan detected file encryption and confirmed that data — including employee W-2 and 1099 information and patient treatment records — had been exfiltrated prior to ransomware deployment. Mandiant was engaged to lead the investigation. Eight Magellan affiliates filed separate HHS breach reports, and over 364,000 individuals were ultimately affected nationally across Magellan's managed behavioral health and pharmacy subsidiaries. A $3.75 million class action settlement resolved the resulting litigation.",
