    "title": "Samaritan Center of Puget Sound Equipment Theft Exposes 20,866 Patient Records",
    "summary": "Samaritan Center of Puget Sound, a nonprofit mental health counseling organization serving the greater Seattle region since 1960, experienced multiple break-ins at its Ravenna Boulevard facility in Seattle over the course of approximately twelve months, during which a computer, server, and other electronic equipment were stolen. The organization completed a review of files stored on the compromised systems around September 3, 2021, confirming that protected health information of current and former patients had been exposed. The breach was reported to HHS OCR as affecting 20,866 individuals. Compromised data included names, addresses, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, state ID numbers, dates of birth, financial account information, medical claim information, medical record numbers, patient account numbers, medical diagnoses, treatment information, and health insurance information. In response, Samaritan Center implemented additional physical security measures including enhanced alarm coverage, video cameras, new locks, and server anchoring to prevent physical removal, and was exploring further data encryption.",
