    "enriched_summary": "Over approximately twelve months, the Samaritan Center of Puget Sound, a nonprofit mental health counseling organization in Seattle's Ravenna neighborhood serving the region since 1960, suffered multiple physical break-ins resulting in the theft of a computer, a server, and other electronic equipment from its office at 564 NE Ravenna Boulevard. A review of files stored on the compromised systems was completed around September 3, 2021, confirming that the protected health information of 20,866 current and former mental health patients was exposed. In response, the organization implemented enhanced alarm coverage, surveillance cameras, new locks, and server anchoring, and explored further data encryption.",
