    "title": "Evergreen Treatment Services Email and OneDrive Account Hack Affects 21,325 Patients",
    "summary": "On or around December 13, 2022, an employee email account and associated OneDrive account at Evergreen Treatment Services — a Seattle-based nonprofit providing addiction counseling, methadone/buprenorphine treatment, and mental health services across Western Washington — were compromised by an unauthorized actor. A forensic investigation determined that the compromised account contained a spreadsheet listing incident reports with patient names, addresses, dates of birth, dates of death, treatment locations, medical record numbers, limited medical information, and medication details. The breach affected 21,325 individuals. Evergreen Treatment Services notified affected patients and offered complimentary credit monitoring and identity theft protection. A $425,000 class action settlement was subsequently reached.",
    "source_url": "https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/all-individuals-notified-by-evergreen-treatment-services-regarding-the-data-incident-that-occurred-in-december-2022-302286428.html",
