    "title": "Premera Blue Cross: Vendor Conduent Breach Exposes Member PHI",
    "summary": "Premera Blue Cross, Washington's largest health insurer headquartered in Mountlake Terrace, notified members that vendor Conduent Business Services suffered a cyberattack from October 21, 2024 through January 13, 2025 in which an unauthorized party accessed files containing Premera member protected health information. Exposed data potentially included member names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, treatment and diagnosis codes, treatment costs, admission/discharge dates, member ID numbers, and claim numbers. The breach originated at Conduent — which provided printing, document processing, and back-office services — and did not directly involve Premera's own IT systems; Conduent's total victim count across all affected clients grew to 25 million-plus individuals nationwide.",
