    "enriched_summary": "Premera Blue Cross, Washington's largest health insurer headquartered in Mountlake Terrace, notified members that vendor Conduent Business Services suffered a cyberattack — attributed to the SafePay ransomware group — during which an unauthorized party maintained persistent access from October 21, 2024 through January 13, 2025 (approximately 84 days). Conduent provided mailroom, document processing, and back-office administrative services for Premera, and the exfiltrated files contained Premera member PHI including names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, diagnosis codes, treatment costs, admission and discharge dates, member ID numbers, and claim numbers. The breach did not directly affect Premera's own IT systems; Conduent's total victim count across all affected healthcare clients grew to 25 million-plus individuals nationally, prompting a Texas Attorney General investigation. Premera notified affected members and offered two years of complimentary credit monitoring.",
