    "title": "Conduent Business Services / Premera Blue Cross: Third-Party Vendor Breach Exposes Health Plan Member Data",
    "summary": "Conduent Business Services, a third-party vendor providing mailroom, document processing, and back-office services to health plans, suffered a cyberattack between October 21, 2024 and January 13, 2025 (discovered January 13, 2025). Premera Blue Cross, a leading Pacific Northwest health insurer, was among the affected clients, with member PHI including names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, diagnosis codes, treatment costs, and claim numbers potentially exposed. The breach was disclosed to the Washington State Attorney General in October 2025, with 76,285 Washington residents confirmed affected across all Conduent clients; the breach ultimately grew to impact at least 25 million Americans nationwide.",
    "source_url": "https://healthsource.premera.com/our-perspective/news/conduent-data-security-incident/",
    "source_name": "Premera Blue Cross / PR Newswire",
