    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "Conduent Business Services, a global business process outsourcing firm providing mailroom, document processing, and back-office services to health insurers, was attacked by the SafePay ransomware group with initial access beginning October 21, 2024 and discovery occurring January 13, 2025 — a dwell time of approximately 84 days and exfiltration of 8.5 terabytes of data. Premera Blue Cross was among the affected clients, with Washington state members' PHI including names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, diagnosis codes, treatment costs, and claim numbers potentially exposed; 76,285 Washington residents were confirmed affected across all Conduent clients. The breach was disclosed to the Washington State Attorney General in October 2025, representing a nearly one-year gap between discovery and state-level notification. Nationwide, the breach grew to impact at least 25 million Americans, triggering a Texas Attorney General investigation and multiple class action lawsuits.",
