    "title": "Navia Benefit Solutions: Washington-Based FSA/COBRA Administrator Breach Exposes 2.7 Million Health Plan Records",
    "summary": "Renton, WA-based Navia Benefit Solutions, a third-party administrator of Health Care FSAs, COBRA, and HRA benefits for over 10,000 employers, suffered a cyberattack from December 22, 2025 to January 15, 2026 via exploitation of a BOLA (Broken Object Level Authorization) API vulnerability. The Washington State Health Care Authority was a key affected client, with approximately 27,000 current and former PEBB members, 5,600 SEBB members, and 3,000 COFA islander members impacted; records dating back to 2018 were compromised including names, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, phone numbers, email addresses, and detailed health plan information. A total of 2,697,540 individuals nationwide were affected, generating multiple class action lawsuits.",
