    "title": "Hi-School Pharmacy Cyberattack Exposes Patient and Employee Data",
    "summary": "On November 2–3, 2023, Hi-School Pharmacy — a Vancouver, Washington-based regional drug store chain — suffered a cyberattack that caused significant network disruption. Digital forensic investigators confirmed attackers accessed the network between November 2 and November 3 and acquired files containing sensitive employee and patient information. Notification letters were mailed to 17,676 affected individuals in December 2023, of which 3,695 were Washington state residents. Compromised data included names, Social Security numbers, full dates of birth, health insurance policy or ID numbers, and medical information. A class action lawsuit was filed in the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Washington in January 2024, and Hi-School Pharmacy agreed to a $600,000 settlement to resolve the litigation. Plaintiffs alleged the pharmacy failed to implement adequate cybersecurity measures including spam filters, firewalls, and regular staff security awareness training.",
