    "title": "Change Healthcare / UnitedHealth Group: ALPHV/BlackCat Ransomware Attack Disrupts Washington State Pharmacies",
    "summary": "On February 21, 2024, ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware actors attacked Change Healthcare (an Optum/UnitedHealth Group subsidiary), the nation's largest healthcare claims clearinghouse, crippling prescription processing for pharmacies nationwide. At least eight Wenatchee Valley pharmacies in Washington state were directly disrupted — including Washington Valley Pharmacy, Columbia Valley Community Health Pharmacy, and branches of Walmart, Albertsons, Costco, Walgreens, Fred Meyer, Safeway, and CVS-affiliated pharmacies — leaving patients unable to fill prescriptions via insurance. The breach ultimately exposed the protected health information of an estimated 192.7 million individuals nationally, including Washington state patients, with Change Healthcare beginning breach notifications in June 2024; Washington's Insurance Commissioner issued a Technical Assistance Advisory to health insurers in response.",
