    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "enriched_summary": "On February 21, 2024, ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware actors deployed ransomware on Change Healthcare systems — the nation's largest healthcare claims clearinghouse — after gaining initial access on February 12 via a Citrix portal lacking multi-factor authentication and spending nine days moving laterally through the network exfiltrating data. At least eight Wenatchee Valley-area Washington state pharmacies experienced direct prescription processing disruption, including community pharmacies and major chains (Walmart, Albertsons, Costco, Walgreens, Fred Meyer, Safeway, CVS), leaving patients unable to fill prescriptions via insurance. The breach ultimately exposed the PHI of an estimated 190–192.7 million Americans — the largest healthcare data breach in U.S. history — and UnitedHealth Group paid $22 million in Bitcoin ransom. Change Healthcare began breach notifications in June 2024 and Washington's Insurance Commissioner issued a Technical Assistance Advisory to health insurers.",
