    "title": "MedImpact Healthcare Systems: Qilin ransomware attack on national PBM serving Washington state health plans",
    "summary": "MedImpact Healthcare Systems, one of the largest independent pharmacy benefit managers in the US serving over 50 million members including state and local government health plans, confirmed a ransomware attack by the Russia-linked Qilin group on October 27, 2025, with notifications and ongoing breach investigation continuing into early 2026. The attack disrupted pharmacy claims adjudication nationally and resulted in exfiltration of approximately 160GB of data including financial records, commission reports, and claims remittance information. As a PBM processing pharmacy benefits for numerous Washington state employer and government health plans, the incident has implications for Washington members, though the company has not publicly quantified state-specific impact.",
