    "enriched_summary": "MedImpact Healthcare Systems, one of the largest independent pharmacy benefit managers in the US serving over 50 million members including state and local government health plans, confirmed a ransomware attack by the Russia-linked Qilin group on October 27, 2025. The attack disrupted pharmacy claims adjudication systems nationally and resulted in exfiltration of approximately 160 GB of data including financial operations records, commission reports, bank account summaries, and claims remittance information. MedImpact engaged a leading cybersecurity firm, rebuilt affected systems within a segregated multi-layered security environment, and restored partial claims processing within days; as a PBM processing pharmacy benefits for numerous Washington state employer and government health plans, the incident has implications for Washington members though state-specific impact counts were not publicly quantified. Qilin claimed this as one of over 700 attack claims in 2025, making it the most active ransomware group that year.",
