    "title": "Asante Health System — Physician Insider Unauthorized Record Access",
    "summary": "Asante, a southern Oregon health system based in Medford, notified 8,834 patients that a non-employed physician with admitting privileges (Dr. Paul Hoffman) inappropriately accessed their electronic health records over an 8.5-year period (June 2014 – January 2023). Asante's investigation, completed February 14, 2023, found numerous accesses without a valid clinical reason. Exposed data included patient names, demographics, diagnoses, and treatment information. No SSNs, financial data, or driver's license numbers were accessed. Asante terminated the physician's EHR access and referred the matter to the Oregon Medical Board. The breach was reported to HHS OCR on February 24, 2023.",
