    "data_types": "['names', 'addresses', 'dates of birth', 'Social Security numbers', \"driver's license numbers\", 'financial information', 'medical information', 'health insurance information', 'digital signatures']",
    "enriched_summary": "The Neuromusculoskeletal Center of the Cascades, PC and affiliated Cascade Surgicenter LLC in Oregon suffered a phishing-driven email account compromise over October 2–3, 2023, exposing highly sensitive patient data including Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, financial information, and digital signatures for nearly 23,000 individuals. The Oregon Attorney General was notified of 22,796 affected individuals, while HHS OCR was separately notified of 19,373 individuals whose PHI was compromised. The organizations settled a resulting class action lawsuit, with class members eligible for up to $2,500 in identity theft/fraud reimbursement, $500 for documented out-of-pocket losses, or a flat $80 cash payment, plus two years of medical data monitoring.",
