    "title": "ORM Fertility Ransomware Attack Exposes Patient Health Information",
    "summary": "Oregon Reproductive Medicine, LLC (d/b/a ORM Fertility), a Portland-based fertility clinic, experienced a ransomware attack on or around August 26–27, 2024. The attack caused a network disruption affecting parts of the company's IT infrastructure. A forensic investigation confirmed that an unauthorized party accessed the network during that window and may have accessed files containing protected health information and other sensitive consumer data. ORM Fertility posted a breach notice on its website on October 25, 2024, and reported the incident to HHS Office for Civil Rights using a placeholder figure of 500 individuals while the investigation was ongoing. The full scope of affected individuals was not publicly confirmed by the end of 2024.",
