    "title": "River City Eye Care Ransomware Attack — Genesis Group Exfiltrates Patient Data",
    "summary": "River City Eye Care, a multi-location ophthalmology practice in Happy Valley and Portland, Oregon, suffered a network intrusion beginning around September 8, 2025. An unauthorized actor copied files from the practice's internal network. The Genesis ransomware group later claimed responsibility, alleging theft of approximately 200 GB of data including medical records, management host data, and file-server content. The practice completed its review on October 1, 2025, and began mailing notification letters on October 16, 2025. Approximately 6,588 patients were notified. Exposed data included names, addresses, email addresses, phone numbers, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, medical information, and financial information. Free credit monitoring through Epiq Privacy Solutions was offered to affected individuals.",
