    "title": "La Pine Community Health Center Patients Exposed via TriZetto Vendor Breach",
    "summary": "La Pine Community Health Center (LCHC), a federally qualified health center in La Pine, Oregon, was among several Oregon healthcare providers affected by a breach at third-party insurance-eligibility verification contractor TriZetto Provider Solutions (TPS). Beginning in November 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed historical eligibility reports stored on TPS systems. The threat was eliminated on October 2, 2025. LCHC was notified on December 10, 2025, and began patient notifications thereafter. Approximately 1,200 LCHC patients were affected. Exposed data may include names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurer names, and health insurance member numbers. LCHC's own systems were not compromised.",
