    "title": "Prestige Care, Inc. — Malware / Ransomware Attack on Senior Care Network",
    "summary": "Prestige Care, Inc., a senior care organization headquartered in Vancouver, Washington, that operates nearly 80 senior care facilities (including skilled nursing, assisted living, and memory care) across the western United States including Oregon, detected suspicious activity and malware on its network on September 7, 2023. An unauthorized actor accessed and potentially exfiltrated files containing personal and protected health information of residents and employees on that date. The file review concluded December 18, 2023, identifying compromised data that included names and Social Security numbers. Prestige Care filed an HHS OCR breach notice on November 6, 2023, affecting 38,087 individuals. Notification letters were mailed to affected individuals beginning January 31, 2024. Prestige Care subsequently settled a class action lawsuit for $700,000.",
