    "title": "Consonus Healthcare Services Breach Exposes Staff Data at Oregon-Based LTC Pharmacy",
    "summary": "Consonus Healthcare Services, headquartered in Milwaukie, Oregon, and a subsidiary of the Marquis Companies senior living chain, experienced a cybersecurity breach between August 9 and August 17, 2024. Consonus provides pharmacy and rehabilitation consulting services to long-term care and senior living facilities across Oregon and seven other states. The breach exposed names, Social Security numbers, and other personal information of approximately 4,800 employees and job applicants. The company delayed notifying affected individuals for over three months, sending letters in November 2024. A class-action lawsuit filed in U.S. District Court in Portland in December 2024 alleged negligence in data security practices. Although the compromised data was primarily employee records rather than patient records, Consonus's role as a pharmacy and consulting services provider to LTC facilities places this incident in the long-term care sector.",
