    "breach_type": "Hacking / Unauthorized Network Access",
    "enriched_summary": "Consonus Healthcare Services, a Milwaukie, Oregon-based rehabilitation pharmacy and consulting company (subsidiary of Marquis Companies senior living chain), experienced unauthorized access to its network between August 9 and August 17, 2024, exposing names, Social Security numbers, and other PII of approximately 4,800 current and former employees and job applicants. The company waited over three months before notifying affected individuals in November 2024, prompting a class action lawsuit filed in U.S. District Court in Portland in December 2024 alleging negligence, failure to monitor systems, and non-compliance with cybersecurity standards. Patient records were not involved, but the incident threatened the operational trust of a company providing pharmacy services across multiple states' senior care facilities.",
