    "title": "Seasons Living Data Breach Exposes Residents, Employees, and Vendors Across Multiple States",
    "summary": "Seasons Living, an independent living, assisted living, and memory care operator headquartered in Lake Oswego, Oregon, detected a data breach on March 4, 2025. The company operates eight senior living communities across Arizona, California, Idaho, Kansas, and Oregon. A cybercriminal known as 'f1y' claimed responsibility for leaking the stolen data. Seasons Living published its breach notice on August 6, 2025, and disclosed the incident to state authorities (including Massachusetts) on August 8, 2025. The total number of affected individuals was not disclosed but is believed to be in the thousands, spanning residents, prospective residents, employees, owners, and vendors across multiple states. Exposed data may include names, addresses, contact information, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, driver's license or state ID numbers, health insurance information, medical records, and financial information. Twelve months of complimentary credit monitoring was offered to affected individuals.",
