    "title": "Oregon State Hospital Patient Census Photo Accidentally Shared by Psychiatrist",
    "summary": "On June 9, 2024, a psychiatrist at Oregon State Hospital (a state psychiatric facility operated by the Oregon Health Authority) used a personal cell phone to photograph a patient census sheet and accidentally transmitted the image to six people outside the hospital. The census sheet contained patient names, identification numbers, treatment information, legal status, precaution and privilege levels, and photos of each patient. The six recipients were asked to delete the image and confirmed they had done so. Hospital officials stated there was no evidence of misuse. The psychiatrist involved underwent retraining on information privacy requirements. The Oregon Health Authority publicly disclosed the incident.",
    "source_url": "https://www.oregon.gov/oha/erd/pages/oha-notify-public-state-hospital-data-breach.aspx",
    "source_name": "Oregon Health Authority",
    "date": "2024-06-09",
    "severity": "low",
