    "healthcare_sector": "Behavioral Health",
    "state": "OR",
    "sled_sector": null,
    "industry": "Healthcare",
    "featured": false,
    "organization": "Oregon State Hospital (Oregon Health Authority)",
    "records_affected": null,
    "breach_type": "Accidental Disclosure / Insider",
    "enriched_summary": "On June 9, 2024, a psychiatrist at Oregon State Hospital — a state psychiatric facility operated by the Oregon Health Authority — photographed a patient census sheet using a personal cell phone and accidentally transmitted the image to six external recipients. The census sheet contained patient names, identification numbers, treatment information, legal status, precaution and privilege levels, and patient photos. All six recipients confirmed deletion of the image, and hospital officials found no evidence of misuse. The incident, while limited in scale, involved a particularly sensitive population of psychiatric patients whose legal status and mental health information were exposed.",
