    "summary": "Best Care, a Bend, Oregon-based behavioral health and substance use disorder services provider, was among three Central Oregon healthcare organizations affected by a breach at TriZetto Provider Solutions, a third-party insurance-eligibility verification contractor. Beginning in November 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed historical eligibility reports on TriZetto's systems. The threat was eliminated on October 2, 2025. Best Care was notified on December 10, 2025, and began notifying affected clients. Approximately 1,650 Best Care clients/patients were affected. Exposed data may include names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurer names, and health insurance member numbers. Medical diagnoses, treatment information, and financial account data were not included. IDX provided 12 months of free credit and CyberScan monitoring with a $1 million insurance reimbursement policy.",
