    "title": "Deschutes County Health Services — 1,300 Patients Exposed via TriZetto Vendor Breach",
    "summary": "Deschutes County Health Services (DCHS), a public health agency in Bend, Oregon that provides behavioral health, public health, and environmental health services, was notified on December 10, 2025 that a breach at third-party contractor TriZetto Provider Solutions had exposed some of its clients' protected health information. Beginning in November 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed historical eligibility reports on TriZetto's systems. The threat was eliminated on October 2, 2025. DCHS will notify approximately 1,300 clients/patients. Exposed data may include names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurer names, and health insurance member numbers. Medical diagnoses and treatment information were not included. IDX provided free identity theft protection services. A class-action lawsuit was subsequently filed.",
