    "title": "BestCare Treatment Services Patient Data Exposed in TriZetto Provider Solutions Breach",
    "summary": "BestCare Treatment Services, a Central Oregon behavioral health and substance use disorder treatment provider with locations in Bend, Redmond, Madras, Klamath Falls, and Prineville, was among three Oregon healthcare organizations whose patient data was exposed through a third-party breach at TriZetto Provider Solutions (TPS). TPS, which provides insurance eligibility verification services, suffered unauthorized access beginning November 2024 and eliminated the threat on October 2, 2025. BestCare notified approximately 1,650 clients in January 2026. Exposed data may include names, addresses, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, health insurer names, health insurance member numbers, and provider names. No medical diagnosis or treatment information, nor financial data, was exposed. TPS's total breach impact exceeded 700,000 individuals nationally.",
