    "title": "CareOregon Mismailing Incident Exposes Member Information of 1,786 Oregon Health Plan Members",
    "summary": "On April 4, 2025, CareOregon discovered that documents intended for a local hospital and its clinics had been mailed to an incorrect address. The documents contained plan members' first and last names, health plan, ID numbers, claim numbers, and the clinic where they received services. Social Security numbers and financial information were not included. The breach was reported to HHS OCR on May 30, 2025 and affected 1,786 individuals, primarily Jackson Care Connect members. CareOregon identified the root cause and implemented new address-verification procedures and staff retraining to prevent recurrence.",
