    "enriched_summary": "On April 4, 2025, CareOregon discovered that documents containing plan member information intended for a local hospital and its clinics had been mailed to an incorrect address. The 1,786 affected members were primarily Jackson Care Connect members. Exposed data included names, health plan, ID numbers, claim numbers, and the clinic where services were received — but no SSNs or financial information. CareOregon identified the root cause, implemented new address-verification procedures, and retrained staff. The incident was reported to HHS OCR on May 30, 2025.",
