    "title": "CareOregon and Health Share of Oregon — Unauthorized Member Data Access, Potential Insurance Fraud",
    "summary": "On October 27, 2025, CareOregon and Health Share of Oregon learned that one or more individuals accessed member information without authorization, with an exposure window spanning May 25 through October 27, 2025. The Oregon DOJ was notified on December 26, 2025. Approximately 8,022 members across three plans were affected: 5,589 CareOregon members, 1,849 Jackson Care Connect members, and 584 Columbia Pacific CCO members. Exposed data included first and last names, dates of birth, health plan information, Medicaid ID numbers, Medicare ID numbers (where applicable), and primary care provider offices. Social Security numbers and financial information were not accessed. CareOregon warned members that information may have been used to create fraudulent insurance claims. Law enforcement was notified; access controls were changed and staff retrained.",
