    "enriched_summary": "On October 27, 2025, CareOregon and Health Share of Oregon discovered that one or more individuals had accessed member information without authorization across a 5-month window (May 25–October 27, 2025), affecting 8,022 members across three plans: 5,589 CareOregon, 1,849 Jackson Care Connect, and 584 Columbia Pacific CCO members. CareOregon explicitly warned that the accessed data — names, DOB, Medicaid and Medicare IDs, and primary care provider information — may have been used to create fraudulent insurance claims. Law enforcement was notified, access controls were changed, and staff were retrained. Oregon DOJ was notified December 26, 2025.",
