    "summary": "Consonus Healthcare Services, a Milwaukie, Oregon-based rehabilitation pharmacy and consulting company (part of the Marquis Companies senior living chain), suffered a cybersecurity breach beginning August 9, 2024 and detected August 17, 2024. The unauthorized access exposed names, Social Security numbers, and other personal information of approximately 4,800 current and former employees and job applicants. Consonus waited over three months before issuing notifications in November 2024. A class-action lawsuit was filed in U.S. District Court in Portland in December 2024, alleging the company was negligent in failing to maintain adequate data security systems. The breach affected employee data, not patient records, but the company provides pharmacy services to rehabilitation and senior care facilities across multiple states.",
